{ "Betwixt the cup and the lip" }
1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Be7 8. Qf3 Nbd7 9. O-O-O Qc7 10. Bd3 (10. g4 b5 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. g5 Nd7 13. f5 Bxg5+ 14. Kb1 Ne5 15. Qh5 { The modern mainline in the Najdorf. }) 10... b5 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. Rhe1 Bb7 (12... b4 13. Nce2 Bb7 14. Kb1 $10) 13. Kb1 Rc8 14. g4 Nd7 15. g5 Nb6?? (15... b4 16. Nce2 Nc5 $10) 16. f5 e5 17. f6! gxf6 (17... exd4?? 18. Nd5! $18 { What Fischer had overlooked. }) 18. gxf6 Bf8 19. Nd5 Nxd5 20. exd5 { Black is completely busted here. } 20... Kd8 21. Nc6+ Bxc6 22. dxc6 Qxc6 23. Be4 Qb6 24. Qh5 Kc7 25. Bf5 Rd8 26. Qxf7+ Kb8 27. Qe6 Qc7 28. Re3 Bh6 29. Rc3 Qb7 30. f7 Bg7 31. Rcd3 Bf8 32. Qxe5! dxe5 33. Rxd8+ Ka7 34. R1d7 h5 35. Rxb7+ Kxb7 36. c3 Kc7 37. Ra8 (37. Re8! $18 { Fischer would have resigned here. Black is already in Zugzwang. }) 37... Kd6 38. Rxa6+ Ke7 39. Re6+ Kxf7 40. Rxe5 b4! { The game was adjourned, but Fischer believed he had swindling prospects... } 41. cxb4 Bxb4 42. h3 Kf6 43. Rb5 Bd6 44. Be4 (44. a4 Rb8! { Opposite colored bishop endings can be easily drawn, even down two pawns! }) 44... Re8 45. Rf5+ Kg7 46. Bf3 Re1+ 47. Kc2 Rf1 48. Rd5 Rf2+ 49. Rd2 (49. Kb1!? Ba3 50. bxa3 Rxf3 51. Rxh5 Rxa3 $18) 49... Rxd2+ 50. Kxd2 h4 { While still completely lost, this opposite colored bishop ending is always going to be black's best hope for a draw. } 51. Kd3 Kf6 52. Kc4 Ke7 53. Kb5 Kd7 54. a4?? (54. b4! Kc7 55. Ka5 Kb8 56. b5 Ba3 57. b6 Kc8 58. Ka6 Kb8 59. Bg2 $18 { Zugzwang. If the bishop moves, a4 wins. If the king moves, Ka7 wins. }) 54... Kc7 55. b4 Kb8 56. a5 Ka7 57. Kc4 Bg3 58. b5 Bf2 $10 { If b6+ if ever played, Bxb6 leads to a draw because the white bishop is the wrong-colored bishop for the h pawn to promote. } 59. Be2 (59. b6+ Bxb6 60. axb6+ Kxb6 61. Kd4 Kc7 62. Ke5 Kd7 63. Kf5 Ke7 64. Kg4 Kf6 65. Kxh4 Kg7 $10) 59... Be3 60. Kb3 Bd2 61. b6+ Kb7 62. Ka4 Kc6 63. Bb5+ Kc5 $10 { 1/2-1/2 The game is a draw. } 64. b7 Bf4 65. a6 Kb6 $10 { Th dark squared blockade cannot be broken. } { [%cal Gb6a7] } 1/2-1/2


