{ "Milking the cow" }
1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 { Another Ruy Lopez. For comments on the first 22 moves, see the similar game Fischer - Shocron, Chapter 7. } 4... Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3 O-O 9. h3 Na5 10. Bc2 c5 11. d4 Qc7 12. Nbd2 Bd7 13. Nf1 Rfe8 14. Ne3 g6 15. dxe5 dxe5 16. Nh2 Rad8 17. Qf3 Be6 18. Nhg4 Nxg4 19. hxg4 Qc6 20. g5 Nc4 21. Ng4 Bxg4 22. Qxg4 f6? { The first new move relative to chapter 7: https://lichess.org/study/miI3fn8S/WAfxZY84#43 } 23. gxf6 Bxf6 24. a4 Nb6 25. axb5 axb5 26. Be3 { On the open board, the two bishops will make themselves felt. } 26... Ra8 (26... Nc4 27. Bb3 $16) 27. Red1 { [%csl Gh6][%cal Gg4h3] } (27. b3!? { [%csl Gc4][%cal Gb6c4] } 27... Rxa1 28. Rxa1 Ra8 29. Rd1 Ra2 30. Bd3 Kg7 $16 (30... c4 31. bxc4 bxc4 32. Bf1 $16 { [%cal Gc4a2,Gc4g8] })) 27... Kh8 28. b3 Bg7 29. Qh4 Bf6 30. Bg5?! { Trading the bishops makes the e pawn weaker. But giving up the bishop pair can't be best... } (30. Qh3!? { But making progress after Red8 isn't easy. }) 30... Bxg5 31. Qxg5 Rxa1 32. Rxa1 Nd7 33. Bd1! Nf6 (33... Qxe4?? 34. Bf3 Qf4 (34... Qc2 35. Ra7! { [%cal Ga7h7,Gg5f6] } 35... Qd3 36. Bg4 $18) 35. Qxf4 exf4 36. Bc6 Re7 37. Ra8+ Kg7 38. Ra7 $18) 34. Ra7 Qd6 (34... Nxe4?? 35. Qh6 $18 { [%cal Gh6g7,Gh6h7] }) 35. Be2 { "Black is in too much of a straightjacket to defend this pawn" } 35... Re7? (35... b4?? 36. Ra6 Nxe4 37. Qh4 Qd5 38. Bf3 Qd3 39. Ra7 $18 { [%cal Gh4h7] }) (35... Nxe4?? 36. Qh6 Re7 37. Qf8#) (35... Qb6?? 36. Rf7 Ng8 37. Qh4 h6 38. Qg4 { Bxb5 deflection is unstoppable. }) (35... Rb8?? 36. Rf7 Ng8 37. Rd7! { [%cal Gg5e5,Ge5b8,Ge5h8] } 37... Qf6 38. Qe3 Qc6 39. Rd5 $18 { [%cal Gd5c5,Gd5e5] }) (35... c4! 36. bxc4 Qb6! 37. cxb5! Qxa7?? (37... Nxe4 38. Rxh7+ Kxh7 39. Qh4+ Kg7 40. Qxe4 $16) 38. Qxf6+ $18) 36. Rxe7 Qxe7 37. Bxb5 Kg7 38. Be2 Qc7 { [%cal Gf6e4] } 39. Qe3 Qa5 40. g3 Qa3 41. Kg2 (41. b4! cxb4 42. Qc5! { [%cal Gc5a3] } 42... Qxc3?? (42... Qa2 43. cxb4 Qxe2 44. Qe7+ Kh6 45. Qxf6 Qe1+ 46. Kh2 Qxb4 47. Qxe5 $16 { This is black's best try in this line. White should be winning due to the passed e pawn, but perpetual check ideas are always tough to stop. }) 43. Qe7+ $18 { [%csl Gf6] }) 41... Qa5 (41... Qxb3? 42. Qxc5 Nxe4 43. Qxe5+ Nf6 44. c4! $18) 42. Qd3 Qb6 43. Qc4 Qc6 44. Bd3 Qb6 45. b4 cxb4 46. cxb4 { The passed b pawn now gets pushed to victory lane! } 46... Ng4 { [%cal Gg4f2,Gb6f2] } 47. Qc5 Qxc5 (47... Qd8?? 48. Be2 $18 { e5 cannot be defended any longer }) 48. bxc5 Kf7 49. f4 Ke7 50. Kf3 Nf6 51. Bb5 Ke6 52. Bc4+ Ke7 53. c6 Ne8 (53... exf4!? 54. gxf4 Ne8 55. e5 Nc7 56. Ke4 Ne8 (56... h5 57. Kf3 Ne8 58. Bd3 Kf7 { [%cal Gf3e4,Ge4e3] } 59. Ke3 Nc7 60. Ke4 Ne8 61. Kd5 Nc7+ 62. Kd6 Ne6 63. Bxg6+ Kxg6 64. Kxe6 $18 { [%cal Gc6c8] } 64... h4 65. c7 h3 66. c8=Q h2 67. Qg8+ Kh6 68. Qh8+ $18 { [%cal Gh8h2] }) 57. Bg8 Kf8 58. Bxh7 Kg7 59. Bxg6 Kxg6 60. f5+ Kg5 61. f6 Kg6 62. Kd5 Kf7 63. Kc5 Ke6 64. Kb6 $18) (53... Kd6?? 54. fxe5+ Kxe5 55. c7 $18) 54. fxe5 h6 55. Ke3 Nc7 56. Kd4 h5 57. Ke3! g5 (57... Ne8 58. Kf4 $18 { [%cal Ge3f4,Gf4g5] }) 58. Be2 h4 59. gxh4 gxh4 60. Bc4 Ne8 61. Kf4 Kd8 62. Kg4 Kc7 63. Bf7 Ng7 64. Kxh4 Kxc6 65. Kg5 $18 { 1-0 Black resigns. } 65... Kd7 66. Kf6 Ne8+ 67. Bxe8+ Kxe8 68. Ke6 $18 { Opposition and white wins. } 1-0


