{ "Castling into it" }
1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Be7 8. Qf3 Qc7 9. O-O-O Nbd7 10. g4 b5 11. Bxf6 (11. Bg2 Bb7 12. Rhe1?! b4 13. Nd5 exd5 14. exd5 Kf8! 15. Nf5 Bd8 $17 { An unjustified piece sacrifice from Bernstein-Fischer, 1957. }) 11... gxf6? (11... Nxf6 12. g5 Nd7 13. f5 Bxg5+ 14. Kb1 Ne5 15. Qh5 { Modern theory goes on from here }) 12. f5! (12. a3!? Bb7 (12... Rb8 { "is sharper" }) 13. f5 e5 14. Nb3 $16) 12... Ne5 13. Qh3 O-O! { The only try, but obviously one fraught with risk... } (13... Bd7 14. g5 b4 15. fxe6 bxc3 16. exd7+ Nxd7 17. b3 $16) 14. Nce2! { Rerouting to further pressure e6 } { [%cal Ge2f4,Gf4e6,Gd4e6] } (14. Qh6 Kh8 15. g5?! (15. Rg1 Rg8 16. Rg3 Qd8 17. Rh3 Rg7 $10) 15... Rg8! 16. g6 fxg6 17. Nxe6 (17. fxe6 Bb7 $10) 17... Bxe6 18. fxe6 Rac8 $10) 14... Kh8 15. Nf4 Rg8 16. Rg1 (16. Be2! d5? (16... Qb7 17. fxe6 (17. Rhe1!?) 17... fxe6 18. Ndxe6 Qxe4 19. Rhe1 Bxe6 20. Nxe6 f5! $13 { Possibly best play. Is black really surviving this? }) 17. fxe6 fxe6 (17... dxe4 18. Nd5 Qc5 19. Nf5 $18) 18. Ndxe6 $18) 16... d5! 17. fxe6 dxe4 18. Nd5 Qc5! 19. Nxe7?! (19. Nf5? Qxg1 { The main difference between this and the other line is that the rook on g1 is actually a target! } 20. Nfxe7 Bxe6 21. Nxg8 Bxg4 22. Qh6 Bxd1 23. Ngxf6 Qg7 24. Qxg7+ Kxg7 25. Kxd1 Rd8 26. Bh3 Nc4 27. Ke2 $10) (19. exf7 Nxf7 20. Nxe7 Qxe7 { "is roughly even" but the engine is completely unimpressed and still believes white's attack will yield dividends: } 21. Be2 Ne5 22. Qh6 Bxg4 23. Bxg4 Nxg4 24. Qf4 Ne5 25. Qxe4 Rad8 26. Rxg8+ Kxg8 $16) 19... Qxe7 20. Nf5 Qxe6 21. Qh6 (21. Rg3 { Preparing the Qh6 idea is much stronger than directly going for it! But black should be able to defend everything with perfect play }) (21. Rd6?? Qxa2! 22. Qh6 Qa1+ 23. Kd2 Nf3+ 24. Ke3 Qxb2 $19 { "Gligoric had originally intended this line, but overlooked Qxb2!" }) 21... Bd7! { Black defends Rd8!! overloading the key defender of the g7 square. } 22. Rd6 Nxg4! 23. Rxg4 (23. Rxe6?? Nxh6 24. Rxg8+ Nxg8 $19) 23... Qxf5 24. Rxg8+ (24. Rf4 Qg5 25. Qxf6+ Qxf6 26. Rdxf6 e3! 27. Re4 (27. Rxf7?? Rg1! 28. Rxd7 e2 29. Rd1! exd1=Q+ 30. Kxd1 Kg7 31. Ke1 Rf8 32. Rxf8 Kxf8 33. Kf2 { "with good drawing prospects" but let's be real - with perfect play, white is dead. }) 27... Rae8 28. Rxe8 Rxe8 29. Kd1 Bg4+ 30. Ke1 Kg7 31. Rf4 h5 32. h3 Bd7 $17 { but there are real drawing chances }) 24... Rxg8? (24... Kxg8! 25. Rxf6 Qe5 $15 { "with an extra pawn and a dominant position" }) 25. Rxf6 Qd5 26. Rd6! Qf5 (26... Qb7?? 27. Qf6+ Rg7 28. Qd8+ Rg8 29. Qxd7 $18) 27. Rf6 Qg5+ { "I should have just contented myself with the draw now" } 28. Qxg5 Rxg5 29. Rxf7 Bg4 30. Kd2 Bf3 31. Ke3 Rg1 32. Bh3 Re1+ 33. Kf4 Bd1 34. Ke5 (34. Re7 Bxc2 35. Bf5 $10 { An easy draw from white's perspective. But now white is trying to play for the win... }) 34... e3 35. Bf5 Rg1 36. Rxh7+ Kg8 37. Rc7 Bg4 38. Bxg4 Rxg4 39. Rc3 e2 40. Re3 Rg2 41. Kd4 e1=Q 42. Rxe1 Rxc2 43. Rb1 Kf7 44. a3 Ke6 45. b3 Rxh2 46. Kc5 Kd7 47. Kb6 Ra2 48. Kxa6 Rxa3+ 49. Kb7 Kd6 50. Kb6 Kd7 51. b4 Rh3 52. Rc1 Rh8?? (52... Rh5! 53. Rc5 Rxc5 54. Kxc5 (54. bxc5 b4 55. Kb7 b3 56. c6+ Kd6 57. c7 b2 58. c8=Q b1=Q+ $10) 54... Kc7 55. Kxb5 Kb7 $10 { Opposition, so black gets the draw. }) 53. Kxb5?? (53. Rc7+ Kd6 54. Rc6+ Kd7 55. Kxb5! Rb8+ 56. Rb6 Rh8 57. Rb7+ Kc8 58. Ka6 Rh6+ 59. Ka7 { And white wins this Lucena because black is not able to get in front of the pawn. } 59... Rg6 60. b5 Rh6 (60... Rg1 61. Rb8+ Kc7 62. b6+ Kd7 63. Ra8! (63. Rb7+ Kd8 64. Rc7 Rb1 65. Rc2 Kd7 66. b7 Ra1+ 67. Kb8 $18 { Lucena proper. }) 63... Rb1 64. b7 $18) 61. b6 Rg6 62. Rh7 $18) 53... Rb8+ 54. Ka4 Ra8+ 55. Kb3 Rc8 56. Rxc8 Kxc8 57. Kc4 Kb8 $10 { 1/2-1/2 The game is a draw. } { A form of distant opposition because the pawn on b4 prevents white from taking back the opposition here. } 1/2-1/2


