{ "A whopper" }
1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Be7 8. Qf3 Qc7 9. O-O-O Nbd7 (9... h6 { "Weak" although this literally transposes into the Browne variation... } 10. Bh4 Nbd7 { [%cal Gf1e2] } 11. Bd3 g5! { What Fischer had missed. The main point of the Brown variation - to secure the e5 square for a black knight. } 12. fxg5 Ne5 13. Qe2 Nfg4 $14 { [%cal Ge7h4] }) 10. g4 b5 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. g5 Nd7 13. Bh3? (13. f5! { The correct idea. This innovation had not yet been found during Fischer's time. } 13... Bxg5+ 14. Kb1 O-O 15. fxe6 $14) 13... b4! 14. Nce2 Bb7?? 15. Kb1?? (15. Bxe6!! { "Speculative" and yet the engine says this is completely winning: } 15... fxe6 16. Nxe6 Qc4 17. Nxg7+ Kf8 18. Rd4! { The idea Fischer missed! } 18... Qxa2 19. Rxb4 { [%cal Gb4b7] } 19... Nc5 20. Rxb7!! Nxb7 21. Nc3 Qf7 22. Nf5 $18 { Down a rook, but white has a dominant position. }) 15... Nc5 16. Ng3 d5 { "I could see from the expression on Smyslov's face that he already thought he was busted." The typical Sicilian freeing move means black is at least equal if not better. } 17. f5 (17. e5? g6!) 17... dxe4 18. Qg4 exf5 19. Ndxf5?? (19. Ngxf5! g6?? (19... Bf8 20. Nb3! Nxb3?? (20... Ne6 $10 { According to the engine equal, but this is not an easy position to untangle... }) 21. axb3 g6 22. Rhf1! $18) (19... O-O 20. Qg3 { [%csl Ge7][%cal Gc7g3,Gf5e7] } 20... Bd8 21. Nd6! $14) 20. Ng7+ Kf8 21. Nge6+! { The coordination on e6 ensures that white can rip open black's king with a winning attack. } 21... Nxe6 22. Nxe6+ fxe6 23. Qxe6 $18) 19... g6 20. Nxe7 (20. Nh6?? Bc8! 21. Qh4 Bxh3 (21... Qe5 22. Bxc8 Rxc8 23. Rhf1 Na4! $19) 22. Qxh3 Bxg5 $15) 20... Qxe7 21. Qf4 O-O 22. Rd6 Rad8 23. Rf6 Rd5 24. Bg4 Nd7?! (24... e3! 25. Re1 Rfd8 26. b3 Rd4 27. Rxe3 Rxf4 28. Rxe7 Rxg4! 29. Rfxf7 Rh4! $19) 25. Rf1 e3 (25... Nxf6?? 26. gxf6 Qe5 27. Qh6 $18 { [%cal Gh6g7] }) 26. b3 Rd2! 27. Bxd7 { Forced, otherwise white has their own mating threats on the weakened white king: } (27. h4?? Nxf6 28. gxf6 Qc5 { [%cal Gc5c2] } 29. Rc1 Qd4 $19 { [%cal Gd4f6,Gd4a1] }) 27... Rxd7 28. Re1 Re8 29. h4 Qc5 30. Qc4 Qxc4 31. bxc4 Rd4 32. c5 Rxh4 33. c6 Bc8 34. Rd6 Rc4 35. Kb2 Kg7 36. Kb3 Rg4 37. Ne2 Re6 38. Red1 Rg2 39. Nf4 Rxd6 40. Rxd6 Rd2 41. Rd3! Rf2 42. Rd4 e2 43. Nd3 Bf5 44. c7 Rf3? (44... Bxd3! 45. c8=Q e1=Q 46. Rxd3 Qb1+ 47. Ka4 Rxc2 $19 { Fischer didn't see this in time pressure. }) 45. c8=Q Bxc8 46. Re4 Bf5 47. Rxe2 Bxd3 48. cxd3 Rxd3+ 49. Kxb4 Rd5 50. Rg2 h6 51. gxh6+ Kxh6 52. a4 g5 53. Rc2 Rd6 54. Kc5 Re6 $19 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


