{ "A long voyage home" }
1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3 g6 4. c4 Bg7 5. Nc3 O-O 6. Qb3 (6. Be2?! c5! $10 7. O-O? (7. cxd5 Nxd5 8. Qb3 Nxc3 9. bxc3 Qc7 10. O-O b6 11. a4 Nc6 $15 { Goglidze - Botvinnik, 1935 } (11... Be6? 12. d5 Bg4 13. h3 Bxf3 14. Bxf3 $16)) (7. dxc5 Qa5 8. cxd5 Nxd5 9. Qxd5 Bxc3+ 10. Bd2 Rd8! 11. Bxc3 Qxc3+ 12. bxc3 Rxd5 $15) 7... cxd4 8. Nxd4 Nc6 9. cxd5 Nxd5 10. Nxd5 Qxd5 11. Bf3 Qc4 12. Nxc6 bxc6 $15) 6... e6 7. Be2 Nc6 8. Qc2! (8. cxd5?! exd5 $10 { Black's locked-in bishop has been liberated and black has extremely active pieces. }) (8. O-O?! Na5! 9. Qa4 Nxc4 10. Bxc4 dxc4 11. Qxc4 $10 { Black has the bishop pair }) 8... dxc4 9. Bxc4 e5! 10. dxe5 Ng4 11. O-O Ncxe5 12. Nxe5 Nxe5 13. Be2 c6 $10 { "The chances are now equal" } 14. f4 (14. e4 Qh4! 15. h3 (15. Be3! g5? { [%cal Ge5g6,Gg6f4] } 16. g3 Qh6 $16 17. Qd2 { [%cal Gd2g5] }) 15... g5! 16. Nd1 (16. f4?? Bxh3!! 17. fxe5 (17. gxh3 Qg3+ 18. Kh1 Qxh3+ 19. Kg1 Qg3+ 20. Kh1 Rad8 { [%cal Gd8d6,Gd6h6] } 21. fxe5 Bxe5 22. Bc4 Rd6! 23. Qg2 Rh6+ 24. Kg1 Bd4+ 25. Rf2 Bxf2+ 26. Kf1 Qxg2+ 27. Kxg2 Bd4 $19) 17... Bxe5 18. gxh3 Qg3+ 19. Kh1 Qh2#) 16... f5! 17. f4 Ng6 18. fxg5 f4! $17) 14... Ng4 15. h3 Bf5 16. e4? { "Provoking a powerful combination" } (16. Qb3 Nf6 17. Qxb7 Ne4 18. Qxc6 Rc8 19. Qa6 Nxc3 20. bxc3 Bxc3 21. Ba3 Bxa1 22. Bxf8 Qxf8 (22... Bd4 { Fischer's recommendation for white "with drawing chances" but he missed a key win instead! }) 23. Rxa1 Qc5! 24. Kf2 Re8! $17 { [%csl Ge3][%cal Gc5f2,Ge8e2] }) 16... Qd4+ 17. Kh1 Nf2+ 18. Rxf2 Qxf2 19. exf5 Bxc3! (19... Rfe8 20. Ne4! Qe1+ 21. Kh2 gxf5 22. Ng3 Bd4?? 23. Be3! { [%cal Ga1e1] }) (19... Bd4 20. Bd2 $18) 20. bxc3 Rae8 { [%csl Ge2][%cal Ge8e2] } 21. Bd3 Re1+ 22. Kh2 Qg1+ 23. Kg3 Rfe8! (23... gxf5?! 24. Bxf5 Rfe8 25. Bxh7+?? (25. Bg4!! { The defensive move that Fischer overlooked! } { [%cal Gg4f3] } 25... R8e3+ 26. Kh4 $18) 25... Kg7 26. Qf5 $19 { Equally winning for black as in the game }) 24. Rb1 (24. Kh4! { The best move; Fischer doesn't even see it in his detailed analysis of this position } 24... Qc5 25. Rb1 Qd6 26. fxg6 hxg6 27. Kg4! b5 $15 { Amazingly there's no decisive blow to white's wayward king. No wonder both players missed this king walk idea... }) (24. fxg6 hxg6 25. Bxg6?? (25. Rb1 R8e3+ (25... f5! { Another important resource missed by Fischer! The threat is Rxc1, removing the defender of the e3 square, and there's a mating net around white's king. }) 26. Bxe3 Rxe3+ 27. Kg4 Qh2 28. Qf2 Rxd3 29. Rb2! Rxc3 30. Rd2 $10) 25... R1e2! 26. Bxf7+ Kh8 27. Qf5 Rxg2+ 28. Kh4 { [%cal Gg2g7] } 28... Qe1+ (28... Rg7 29. Qh5+ Rh7 30. Bxe8 Rxh5+ 31. Bxh5 $10 { [%cal Gh5g4,Gh4g5,Gc1b2] }) 29. Kh5 Kg7!! { [%cal Ge8h8] } 30. Bxe8 Qxe8+ 31. Kh4 Qd8+ $19 { [%cal Gd8h8] }) 24... gxf5 25. Bd2 Rxb1 26. Qxb1 Qxb1 27. Bxb1 Re2! $19 { 0-1 White resigns. } { as one of the bishops is lost by force. } 28. Bc1 Re1 $19 { [%cal Ge1b1] } 0-1


