{ "Bad judgement" }
1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 O-O 5. Bg5 d6 6. Qd2 c5 { Fischer elects the Benoni-style KID against this variation. } 7. d5 e6 8. Bd3 exd5 9. Nxd5 (9. cxd5 a6 10. a4 Qa5 11. Nge2 (11. Ra3! Re8 12. Nge2 Nbd7 13. Ng3 Qb4 14. O-O c4 15. Be2 Nc5 { Black gets everything they want in this benoni }) 11... b5 12. O-O b4 $10) 9... Be6 10. Ne2 Bxd5 { Forces white to recapture with a pawn so that the d pawn is not backwards on an open file. } 11. exd5 (11. cxd5 c4 12. Bc2 Nbd7 13. O-O Nc5 14. Nc3 b5! $15 { [%cal Gf6e4,Gc5e4] }) 11... Nbd7 12. O-O Ne5 13. f4?! Nxd3 14. Qxd3 h6 15. Bh4 Re8 16. Rae1 Qb6 17. Bxf6 (17. b3 Ne4! { White has a bind on the weakened e4 square. } 18. Nc1 (18. Ng3?? Bd4+ 19. Kh1 Nf2+ 20. Rxf2 Rxe1+ $19) 18... f5 $17) 17... Bxf6 18. f5 g5 19. b3 Qa5 { [%cal Ga5a2] } 20. Rc1? (20. a4?? Bd4+ { [%cal Ga5e1,Ge8e1] } 21. Kh1 Re3 22. Qd1 Rae8 $19 { A decisive pin on the e file. }) (20. Qb1! b5 $17) 20... Qxa2 21. Rc2 Re3! 22. Qxe3 Qxc2 23. Kh1 a5 24. h4 a4 { 0-1 White resigns. } { White resigned rather than lose every pawn he ever owned: } 25. bxa4 (25. hxg5 Bxg5 $19 { [%cal Ga4b3,Gb3b2,Gb2b1] }) 25... Qxc4 26. hxg5 hxg5 $19 { [%csl Ga4][%cal Ga8a4,Gc4d5,Gc4f1] } 0-1


