{ "When the Maroczy didn't bind" }
1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. f3 Nc6 (5... e5 6. Nb3 d5 7. Bg5 Be6 8. Bxf6 gxf6 9. exd5 Qxd5 10. Qxd5 Bxd5 11. Nc3 Be6 $10) 6. c4 e6 7. Nc3 Be7 8. Be3 O-O 9. Nc2?! { Avoiding piece trades is usually correct when you have a space advantage, but developing your pieces asap is more important here... } 9... d5! { With his lead in development, Fischer immediately breaks through with this typical pawn sac } 10. cxd5 exd5 11. Nxd5 (11. exd5 Nb4 12. Bc4 Qc7 { [%cal Gc7c4] } 13. Bb3 Bc5 14. Bxc5 Qxc5 $10 { [%cal Gc5g1,Gf8e8,Ge8e1] }) 11... Nxd5 12. Qxd5?! (12. exd5 Nb4 13. Bc4 (13. Nxb4?! Bxb4+ $17) 13... Bf5 14. Nd4 (14. Nxb4?? Bxb4+ 15. Kf1 (15. Kf2 Qh4+ { [%cal Gh4c4] }) 15... Re8 $17) 14... Bg6 15. O-O Nxd5 $15 { White has to give back the pawn with tempo in order to castle. Black is comfortable here. }) 12... Qc7 13. Qb5 (13. Be2 { The alternative suggested by Fischer } 13... Bh4+ (13... Rd8! 14. Qb5 Bd7! $17 { Preventing O-O due to Nd4! } 15. O-O?? Nd4 { [%cal Gd7b5,Gd4e2,Gd4c2] } 16. Qd3 Nxc2 17. Rac1 Ba4 { [%cal Gd8d3,Ga4c2] } 18. Rxc2 Qxc2 $19) 14. g3 Bf6 15. O-O Bxb2 16. Rab1 $10 { Fischer's suggestion only gives black equality. }) 13... Bd7 14. Rc1 Nb4! 15. Nxb4 { The best of several bad alternatives. Always sac the exchange. } (15. Qe2 Nxa2! { [%cal Ga2c1] }) (15. Qc4 Qa5 { [%cal Ga5e1] } 16. Nxb4 (16. Kf2 Rac8 17. Qe2 Nxa2 18. Ra1 Bf6 $19 { [%cal Gf6b2] }) 16... Bxb4+ 17. Kf2 Rac8 18. Qd5 Rxc1 19. Bxc1 Be1+! $19) 15... Qxc1+ 16. Bxc1 Bxb5 17. Nd5 Bh4+ 18. g3 Bxf1 19. Kxf1 (19. gxh4 Bc4) 19... Bd8 { "The smoke clears. But there are still great technical difficulties. White's knight is on a dominating outpost and his pawn structure is solid." } 20. Bd2 Rc8 21. Bc3 f5 { Breaking open the position for the rooks is always necessary. } 22. e5 Rc5 23. Nb4 { [%cal Gf5f4] } 23... Ba5 24. a3 Bxb4 25. axb4 (25. Bxb4? Rc1+ 26. Kg2 Rxh1 27. Kxh1 Rc8 { [%cal Gc8c2] } 28. Bc3 g5! $17) 25... Rd5 26. Ke2 Kf7 27. h4 (27. f4 Ke6 28. Ra1 a6 29. h4 h5 30. Ra3 Rc8 $19 { The rooks will eventually be able to infiltrate. } { [%cal Gc8c4,Gc4e4] }) 27... Ke6 28. Ke3 Rc8 29. Rg1 Rc4 30. Re1?? (30. Ra1 a6 31. Rg1) 30... Rxc3+ 31. bxc3 Rxe5+ 32. Kd2 Rxe1 33. Kxe1 { A won king and pawn ending: } 33... Kd5 34. Kd2 Kc4 35. h5 b6 36. Kc2 g5 37. h6 (37. hxg6 hxg6 $19 { [%cal Ga7a5] }) 37... f4 38. g4 a5 { Black can create a passed a pawn in which case the white king is forced to abandon the rest of the kingside pawns in order to stop its advance. } 39. bxa5 bxa5 40. Kb2 a4 41. Ka3 Kxc3 42. Kxa4 Kd4 43. Kb4 Ke3 $19 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


