{ "Time will tell" }
1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. Nc3 (5. c4!? { My personal choice is to take the Maroczy bind here when allowed. }) 5... Bg7 6. Be3 Nf6 7. Be2?! { Does not fight for an advantage, to be perfectly honest. Apparently, Fischer had also played Bc4 in two games during this exact match. } (7. Bc4 O-O 8. Bb3! (8. f3? Qb6 { [%cal Gb6e3,Gb6b2] } 9. Bb3 Nxe4! $15 { [%cal Gg7d4,Gc6d4,Gb6d4] })) 7... O-O 8. f4 (8. O-O?! d5! 9. exd5 Nxd5 $10 { Jobava, Ba - Vachier Lagrave, M., 1/2-1/2, 77th Tata Steel GpA, 2015, https://lichess.org/17qO05Cy }) 8... d6 (8... d5? 9. e5 Ne4 10. Nxe4 dxe4 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Qxd8 Rxd8 13. Bc4 $16) 9. Nb3 Be6 (9... a5 10. a4 Be6 11. O-O Rc8 $10) 10. g4 d5?! (10... Rc8 11. g5 Nd7 12. h4 Nb4 13. Nd4 Bxa2 14. Nxa2 Bxd4 15. Bxd4 Nxc2+ 16. Kf1 e5! 17. fxe5 dxe5 18. Bf2 Nxa1 19. Qxa1 $10) 11. f5 Bc8 12. exd5 Nb4 13. Bf3! { A "modern" and engine approved way forward. White maintains the d5 pawn and exposes black's king in exchange for sacrificing the two kingside pawns. } 13... gxf5 14. a3 fxg4 15. Bg2 Na6 16. Qd3 e6!? (16... Nd7 17. O-O-O Ne5 18. Qe2 $16 { "black's game is lifeless" }) 17. O-O-O Nxd5 18. h3! g3 (18... gxh3?? 19. Rxh3 $18 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gh3h7] }) 19. Rhg1 Qd6 (19... Qh4!? 20. Bxd5 exd5 21. Ne2 Bxh3 22. Nxg3 $16 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gg3f5,Gg1g8,Gb3d4,Gd4f5] }) 20. Bxd5 exd5 21. Nxd5 (21. Bd4?! Bxd4 22. Rxg3+?? { "Nowadays I would have played this without giving it a second thought." JOKES ON YOU. This entire concept is busted. } 22... Bg7 23. Rdg1 Kh8 24. Rxg7 Qf4+ 25. Kb1 Bf5 $17 { [%cal Gf5g6] }) 21... Kh8 22. Bf4 Qg6 23. Qd2? (23. Qe2! { Solves all the problems - by controlling g4 and c2, white is sure to break through on the g file. } 23... Bxh3? 24. Rxg3 $18 { [%cal Gh3g4,Gg3g4,Ge2g4] }) (23. Qf3?! Bf5 { [%cal Gf5c2] }) 23... Bxh3! 24. Rxg3 Bg4! { Black is able to create a blockade because white is missing the light squared bishop to challenge the g4 square. } { [%cal Gf7f5,Gh7h5] } 25. Rh1 Rfe8 26. Ne3 Qe4?? (26... Qf6?? 27. Nxg4! Qxb2+ 28. Kd1 Rad8 29. Rd3 $18) (26... f5! { [%cal Gd2h2,Gh8g8] } 27. Qg2 (27. Qh2 Kg8 $14) 27... Qf6 28. c3 Rac8 29. Kb1 $18 { Best play. Black's attack is stopped, and so white can continue to crash through on the g file. }) 27. Qh2! { "Now the roof caves in." } 27... Be6 (27... Bf5 { The last try, but white is already breaking through anyway. } 28. Rxg7! Kxg7 29. Nxf5+ Qxf5 30. Nd4! { [%cal Gf5g6,Gh1g1] } (30. Qh6+?? Kh8 31. Nd4 Qg6 $10) 30... Qe4 (30... Qg6 31. Rg1 $18) 31. Qh6+ Kg8 32. Rg1+ Qg6 33. Rxg6+) 28. Rxg7 Kxg7 29. Qh6+ Kg8 (29... Kh8 30. Be5+! $18 { A final deflection seals the deal, highlighting why Bf5 was a better try. } { [%cal Gh6h7] }) 30. Rg1+ Qg6 31. Rxg6+ fxg6 32. Nd4 Rad8 33. Be5 Rd7 34. Nxe6 Rxe6 35. Ng4 Rf7 36. Qg5 Rf1+ 37. Kd2 h5 38. Qd8+ $18 { 1-0 Black resigns. } { Reshevsky resigned rather than allow the following: } 38... Rf8 39. Nh6+ Kh7 40. Qxf8 Rxe5 41. Nf7 $18 1-0


