{ "The missing link" }
1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. h3 g6!? { Transposing to a dragondorf is an interesting idea because the tempo on h3 is now officially useless due to the eventual desire for h4-h5 to break on the kingside. } 7. g4 Bg7 8. g5 (8. Be3 O-O 9. Bg2 { Carlsen, Magnus - Ponomariov, Ruslan, 1-0, Moscow Tal Memorial Blitz, 2008, https://lichess.org/KblNSEH9 }) 8... Nh5 9. Be2 e5! (9... Nc6 { Fischer expected this move instead. } 10. Nb3 $10 (10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. Bxh5 gxh5 12. Qxh5 Rb8 $10)) 10. Nb3 Nf4 { The KID-type maneuver. If the knight stays on f4 forever, it is a strong piece. If it is taken, the dark squares are black's forever. } 11. Nd5 Nxd5 12. Qxd5 Nc6 13. Bg4 Bxg4 (13... Qc7!? 14. c3 O-O 15. Be3 b5 { Black can maybe hope to play this position for a win. }) 14. hxg4 Qc8 { [%cal Gc6b4,Rb4c2,Rc8g4,Rb4d5] } 15. Qd1 { Forced. It's clear black is fine here. } 15... Nd4? (15... O-O!? 16. c3 Ne7 17. Be3 Rd8 18. Qf3 d5 19. Qh3! { White can abandon the grip on the d5 square and use the open h file instead. }) (15... d5!? 16. exd5 Nb4! 17. c3 Qc4! 18. Rh3 (18. cxb4? Qe4+ $17 { [%cal Re4h1,Re4e1] }) 18... Nxd5 19. Qe2 Qc7 $10) 16. c3 Nxb3 17. axb3 Qe6 18. Ra5! { Fischer keeps the blockade on d5, and therefore dooms Reshevsky to a bad ending. } 18... f6 (18... O-O 19. Rd5 Rad8 { Fischer preferred this line to the game. Counterplay will occur after f5. } { [%cal Gf7f5] }) 19. Qd5 Qxd5 20. Rxd5 Kd7 21. gxf6 Bxf6 22. g5! { Freezing the kingside pawn majority. } { [%csl Gh7,Gg6] } 22... Be7 23. Ke2 Raf8 24. Be3 Rc8 { White should be able to convert this due to the principle of two weaknesses: d6 and h7 are both fixed targets. } 25. b4 b5!? (25... Ke6 26. Kd3 Kd7 27. c4 $16 { If b5 is not played, white can carry out the threat of c5, pinning and winning this d6 weakness. }) 26. Rdd1 { [%csl Ga6,Gd6,Gh7] } 26... Ke6 27. Ra1 Rc6 28. Rh3 Bf8 (28... d5!? { Active defense should definitely be preferred to the passive defense chosen by Reshevsky in the game. However, the post-mortem showed that white should already be winning. } 29. exd5+ Kxd5 30. Rah1 Kc4 31. Rxh7 Rxh7 32. Rxh7 Re6 33. Kd2 Kb3 34. Kd3 Kxb2 35. Ke4! Kxc3?? (35... Bf8 36. Rh8 Bg7 37. Rg8 Re7 38. Rc8! { "should win" due to the better king, bishop, and rook compared to all of black's counterparts. Black has kept all of his weaknesses, even far into the endgame. } { [%cal Gc8c6,Rc6a6,Rc6g6] }) 36. Kd5 Rd6+ 37. Kxe5 Bf8 38. Rc7+! Kb3 39. Rc8! Be7 40. Re8 Rd7 41. Ke6 { Wins a piece. }) 29. Rah1 Rc7 30. Rh4 { Zugzwang. } 30... d5 (30... Rb7?? { Any rook move along the 7th loses the a pawn. } 31. Ra1! $18 { [%cal Ga1a6] }) (30... Rc8?? 31. Rxh7 $18 { Any rook move along the c file loses the h pawn. }) (30... Rc4!? 31. f3 Rc7 32. Kf2 { Again a zugzwang and black will have to play as in the game. } 32... d5 33. Ra1 Rc6 34. exd5+ Kxd5 35. Rd1+ Ke6 36. Rd8 $18) 31. Ra1! (31. exd5+ Kxd5 32. Rd1+? Ke6 33. Rd8 Bg7! { No breakthrough here, although white remains slightly better. }) 31... Rc6 32. exd5+ Kxd5 33. Rd1+! Ke6 34. Rd8 Kf5 (34... Bg7?? { Now this move loses the h pawn and gives white the most }) (34... Rc7?? 35. Ra8 { [%cal Ga8a6] } 35... Rc6 36. Rh1 $18 { [%cal Gh1a1,Ra1a6] }) 35. Ra8 Re6 36. Rh3! { Threatening a skewer on the f file! } { [%cal Rf3f8] } 36... Bg7 (36... Kg4 37. Rg3+ Kh5 38. Rf3 Bg7 39. Rxh8 Bxh8 40. Rf8 Bg7 41. Rf7 Bh8 42. Rxh7+ $18 { Equally crushing. }) 37. Rxh8 Bxh8 38. Rxh7 { Fischer infiltrates and wins the game immediately. } 38... Re8 39. Rf7+ Kg4 (39... Ke4 40. f3+ Kd5 41. Kd3 $18) 40. f3+ Kg3 41. Kd3 (41. Kf1!! { Bf2+ is an unstoppable mate threat. Black has to give up a piece just to avoid getting mated. } 41... a5?? 42. Bf2+ Kh3 43. Rh7#) 41... e4+ 42. fxe4 Rd8+ 43. Bd4 Kg4 44. Rf1 Be5 (44... Kxg5? 45. Rg1+ Kf4 (45... Kh5?? 46. Rh1+ $18 { [%cal Gh1h8] }) 46. Rxg6 $18) 45. Ke3 Bc7 46. Rg1+ Kh4 47. Kf3 Rd7 (47... Rf8+ 48. Bf6 Kh3 49. Rh1+ Bh2 50. e5 $18) 48. e5 Rf7+ 49. Ke4 Rf5 50. e6 Bd8 51. Bf6! { Gaining control of the e7 square and promoting or: } 51... Bxf6 52. gxf6 Rxf6 53. Kd5! Rf2 54. Re1 $18 { 1-0 Black resigns. } { [%cal Ge6e8] } 1-0


