{ "Tour de force" }
1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. b4 { The second Evans gambit of this book. Check out https://lichess.org/study/miI3fn8S/jtN66eud for his masterpiece against Fine. } 4... Bxb4 5. c3 Be7 6. d4 d6?! { Too slow. } (6... Na5 7. Nxe5 (7. Be2!? { Kasparov revived this line 20 years after this book was written with this move - not recapturing the free pawn. }) 7... Nxc4 8. Nxc4 d5! $10) 7. dxe5?! (7. Qb3! Na5 8. Bxf7+ Kf8 9. Qa4 Kxf7 10. Qxa5 $14) 7... Nxe5? (7... Bg4! $10 { Another way black can return the pawn for development. }) 8. Nxe5 dxe5 9. Qh5! (9. Qb3?! Be6 10. Bxe6 fxe6 11. Qxe6 (11. Qxb7 Nf6 $10) (11. Ba3?? Qd3 $19) 11... Qd6 $10) 9... g6 10. Qxe5 Nf6 11. Ba3! { Now black cannot castle, and so king safety will be a perpetual problem. Moreover, black has no way to get relief either because of the pins in the position and the powerful diagonals white's bishops have taken up. } { [%cal Bc4g8,Ba3f8,Be5e8] } 11... Rf8 (11... Kf8?? 12. Qxf6 $18) (11... Be6! 12. Bxe6 O-O!! 13. O-O Re8! { With a double attack on both bishops miraculously saves black. } 14. Qb5!? $14) 12. O-O Ng4?! (12... Nd7 { Fischer's recommendation, but black isn't solving any of his problems... } { [%cal Gd7b6] }) 13. Qg3 Bxa3 14. Nxa3 Qe7 15. Bb5+ c6 (15... Bd7 16. Bxd7+ Qxd7 17. Rad1 Qe6 18. Nb5 $18 { [%cal Gb5c7] }) 16. Nc4 { Focusing on the d6 square - newly weakened by Bb5+ } { [%cal Gc4d6] } 16... Qe6?? (16... cxb5 { Fischer's down a "piece" but in actuality is up two rooks, given the following attack: } 17. Nd6+ Kd8?? { Fischer only analyzed one attempt to save the game here, and indeed it's lost. } (17... Kd7! 18. Rfd1 Kc6!! $10 { A second miraculous save, confirmed by the engine. White keeps an attack against the obviously weak king, but surprisingly there's no knockout. }) 18. Rfd1 Bd7 19. Nxb7+ Kc8 20. Nd6+ Kd8 21. Rd4 Ne5 22. Rad1 Kc7 (22... g5 23. Nf5 Qe8 24. Qxe5! Qxe5 25. Rxd7+ Ke8 (25... Kc8 26. Ne7+ Kb8 27. Nc6+ Kc8 28. Nxe5 $18) 26. Re7+!! Qxe7 27. Ng7#) 23. f4 Ng4 24. h3 Nf6 25. f5 { [%cal Gg3c7] } 25... Kb6 26. Qe3 { [%cal Ge3b6] } 26... Kc7 27. Rc4+ bxc4 28. Qc5+ Kd8 (28... Bc6 29. Nb5+ $18 { [%cal Gc5e7] }) 29. Qa5#) 17. Rad1 { Morphy style - get all the pieces into the game. } 17... cxb5 (17... Bd7 18. Nd6+ Ke7 19. Bc4 $18) 18. Qc7 { [%cal Gc7d8] } 18... Bd7 19. Nd6+ Ke7 20. Nf5+! { Now the e file will be opened and the last piece will enter the game with devastating effect. } { [%csl Gf1] } 20... gxf5 (20... Ke8?? 21. Ng7+ { [%cal Gg7e6] } 21... Ke7 22. Nxe6 $18) (20... Kf6 21. Rd6 gxf5 22. Qxd7! $18) 21. exf5 Rac8 22. Rxd7+! Qxd7 23. f6+! { "When you see a good move, look for a better one." -Lasker } (23. Re1+ { Equally winning, but not nearly as nice. } 23... Ne5 24. Rxe5+ Kf6 25. Qxd7 Kxe5 26. Qxb5+ $18 { But this requires some work still. }) 23... Nxf6?? (23... Kxf6 24. Qxd7 $18) 24. Re1+ Ne4 25. Rxe4+ Kf6 26. Qxd7 Rfd8 27. Qg4 $18 { 1-0 Black resigns. } (27. Qe7+ { was a faster mate though: } 27... Kf5 (27... Kg6 28. Rg4+ Kf5 (28... Kh5 29. Qg5#) (28... Kh6 29. Qg5#) 29. Rg5+ Kf4 30. Qe5#) 28. Re5+ Kf4 29. Qg5#) 1-0


[Event "Havana"]
[Site "Havana CUB"]
