 Kg4 Kg6 59. Kxh4 h5 $10)) 55. Rxe5! Bxe5 56. Kxe5 $18 { My king cannot get around white's king and touch the g pawn. }) 54. Ra7+ { [%clk 0:04:00] } 54... Kf8?! { I incorrectly thought that any time Kf6 is played, I can kick the king out with Bg5+. Unfortunately that hangs the e pawn. } { [%clk 0:01:00] } (54... Ke8!? { The best try. At least black is fighting here. } 55. Kf6!? (55. Ke6?! Kd8 56. Rf7 Bg3 $18 { It's not so easy for black to enter a winning king and pawn endgame yet. }) 55... Bg3 56. Re7+ Kd8 57. Ra7 $16 { Still work to be done for white. } (57. Rxe5?? { Once more we get the same endgame. } 57... Bxe5+ 58. Kxe5 Ke7 59. Kf4 Kf6 60. Kg4 Kg6 61. Kxh4 h5! $10)) (54... Kg8?! 55. Kg6 Kf8 56. Rf7+! Kg8 57. Rxf4! exf4 58. Kxh6 { Another simple win. } 58... Kf7 59. Kg5 Ke6 60. Kxh4 Kf5 61. Kh5 Kf6 62. Kg4 Ke5 63. h4 $18) 55. Kf6 { [%clk 0:04:00] } 55... Kg8?! { Now my king is stuck towards the corner. I still thought I was fine here during the game though. } { [%clk 0:00:30] } (55... Bg5+?! 56. Kxe5 $18 { Now my king is truly not getting out since every king and pawn endgame is lost. }) (55... Ke8!? { Better defense, although once again I was afraid that Re7+ lead to a winning king and pawn endgame. } 56. Kg6! { Starting a triangulation that wins a tempo is the way forward. The pressure on the h pawn prevents Bg3 as a defensive idea. } 56... Bg5 57. Ra5 Bf4 58. Ra4! { Now Rxf4 is threatened. } 58... Bg5!? (58... Ke7?! 59. Rxf4! exf4 60. Kxh6 $18) (58... Bg3?! 59. Kxh6 $18) 59. Kf5! Bf4?! 60. Rxf4! exf4 61. Kg6! $18) 56. Rb7 { [%clk 0:04:00] } 56... Bg3 { [%clk 0:00:30] } 57. Rb8+ { [%clk 0:04:00] } 57... Kh7 { [%clk 0:00:30] } 58. Kf7 { I still didn't see the win. } { [%clk 0:04:00] } 58... Bf4 { [%clk 0:00:30] } 59. Re8 { Whenever I get a chance to dream of playing e4, she prevents me before it's possible. } { [%clk 0:04:00] } 59... Bg3 { [%clk 0:00:30] } 60. Rg8! { I still didn't see the win. } { [%clk 0:04:00] } 60... Bf4 { [%clk 0:00:30] } 61. Rg7+! { The key finesse. My king is trapped in the corner. } { [%clk 0:04:00] } 61... Kh8 { [%clk 0:00:30] } 62. Kg6! { Only now did I see the win. White will move the rook along the 7th rank and threaten Ranything8#. There's no zuzgwang required even though my king is not in opposition with her king because I am stuck on the corner of the board.
I thought it would be nice to play out the mate to give her the satisfaction of playing such an impressive endgame. } { [%clk 0:04:00] } 62... e4 { [%clk 0:00:30] } 63. Re7 { [%clk 0:04:00] } 63... Bd6 { [%clk 0:00:30] } 64. Re8+ { [%clk 0:04:00] } 64... Bf8 { [%clk 0:00:30] } 65. Rxf8# { 1-0 White wins. } { We were the final board in the top section to finish. Unfortunately my opponent continued to look unhappy even after winning the game. Not sure what was going on with her, but when I jokingly said "I guess there's not really time to analyze this one before our next round," she just scoffed and walked away. } { [%clk 0:04:00] } 1-0


