2... b6? { Just as g6 should only be paired with Bg7, b6 should only be paired with Bb7. How do we show black that there is a tactical flaw to their last move, which weakened the (seemingly strong) light squares? } 3. cxd5 (3. c5? $10 { After Bc7, this move doesn't weaken the light squares in any way. }) 3... cxd5 4. Nxd5! exd5 5. Qxd5+ Qe6 6. Qxa8 $18 { Excellent job!
PRO TIP: Whenever the b pawn (or g pawn) is touched in the opening before the rooks can develop, your tactical antenna should go off. There might just be a way to break through to that trapped rook. } *


[Event "Light and Dark Squares | Master color complex strategy!: Weakening the kingside"]
[Date "2023.03.28"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
