{ My first OTB game. This entire event I was unrated. }
1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 { [%csl Gb4][%cal Gb1c3] } 3... d5 4. g3 { [%csl Gd5,Gc6,Gb7][%cal Gc7c6] } 4... Be7 5. Qc2 O-O 6. Bg2 { I dislike these Catalan structures, as I always feel like black is constantly fighting just to keep it equal. Basically the only way to play is extremely calmly, hoping to trade off all the pieces. } { [%cal Gg2a8] } 6... c6 (6... c5!? 7. cxd5 (7. dxc5 d4) 7... cxd4 8. dxe6 (8. Nxd4 Nxd5 { I missed this idea in the game. } 9. O-O Nb4 10. Qc3 e5! 11. Nc2 N8c6 12. Nxb4 Bxb4 13. Qc4 Be6 14. Qb5 Qe7 15. Bxc6 bxc6 16. Qxe5 $10) 8... Bxe6) 7. O-O b6 { [%cal Gc8b7,Gc6c5] } 8. b3 Nbd7 9. Nc3 Bb7 (9... Ba6 10. Nd2 Rc8 { [%cal Gc6c5] } (10... b5! $10 11. c5? b4 $17) 11. e4 c5 12. exd5 cxd4 13. dxe6 fxe6 14. Nce4 Nc5) 10. Rd1 { My entire goal is to get in the c5 break. Yet achieving it is always difficult with my queen opposite his rook. } 10... Rc8 11. e4 dxe4 12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Qxe4 Nf6 14. Qe2 Qc7 15. Bf4 Bd6 16. Bg5 Be7 { Unless I can get in c5, all I can hope for is a draw right now. } 17. Rac1 Rfd8 18. Ne5 c5! { Dangerous, but I think it works here. } 19. dxc5 (19. d5 Nxd5 (19... exd5 20. Ng4 d4 $15) 20. cxd5 Bxg5 { I thought that d5 didn't work here because of this line, but missed the continuation of d6! } 21. d6!!) 19... Bxc5 20. Bxb7 Qxb7 21. Bxf6 Rxd1+?? (21... gxf6 22. Qg4+ Kf8 23. Qh4 { I saw this line, and was worried that I couldn't capture the knight because of my hanging rook. However, only after white commits with Qh4 is where I can trade the rooks. } (23. Rxd8+ Rxd8 24. Qh4 { I also hallucinated here that he'd have a rook on the d file, and so again I would be losing the exchange if I wasn't careful. }) 23... Rxd1+! 24. Rxd1 fxe5 $10) 22. Rxd1 gxf6 23. Qg4+ Kf8 24. Rd7 Rc7 25. Rxc7?? (25. Rd8+ Ke7 26. Qg8! { This was the move that we both had missed! } 26... fxe5 27. Qg5+ f6 28. Qg8! $18 { Very tough line to spot, but black is now getting mated by force. }) 25... Qxc7 26. Nd3 Be7 27. Qe4 Kg7 28. Nf4 Qe5 { For the first time this game, I'm hopeful that I actually have some chances to win in the resulting knight vs bishop endgame. } (28... f5?? 29. Qxe6 { [%cal Gf4e6,Ge6g7,Ge6c7] } 29... Qxf4 30. Qxe7 { I missed this tactic for a few minutes after getting to the previous move. }) 29. Qb7 Bc5 { [%cal Ge5e1,Ge1f2] } 30. Nd3 { [%cal Gd3f2,Gd3e5,Gd3c5,Gd3e1] } 30... Qa1+ 31. Kg2 Qxa2 { [%cal Gd3c5] } 32. Nf4?! { My opponent was still trying to win. } (32. Nxc5 bxc5 { I was reasonably sure that this was a draw, but the computer seems to suggest that I have something here. } 33. Qb5 a6!? 34. Qxc5 Qxb3 $15) 32... Qxf2+ 33. Kh3 Qe1 { [%csl Ge6] } (33... e5 34. Nh5+ Kg6 35. g4 Qf1+ 36. Kg3 Bf2+ 37. Kf3 $19) 34. Nh5+ Kg6 35. Nf4+ Kg5! { No fear! } 36. Qf3 f5 37. Nd3?? (37. Qh5+ Kf6 38. Qh4+ { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gf4d3] } 38... Kg7 39. Nh5+ Kg6 (39... Kf8?? 40. Qd8#) (39... Kg8?? 40. Qg5+ $18) 40. Nf4+ Kg7 { Sadly, here it's still just a draw. }) 37... Qe4 38. Qf1 Bd6 { I want to trade queens (so that there's no more fears of perpetual checks), but I would like to keep the minor pieces on if possible. } 39. Qc1+ Kg6 40. Qd1 Qg4+ { This move trades off the queens at the expense of a pawn just so that I could get to a minor piece endgame I felt was winning. } 41. Qxg4+ fxg4+ 42. Kxg4 h5+ 43. Kf3 f5 44. h3 (44. Nf4+ Bxf4 45. gxf4 Kf6 46. Ke3 e5 $19) 44... e5 45. Nc1 Kf6 46. Ne2 e4+ 47. Kg2 Be5 { Every king and pawn endgame here should be completely winning. } 48. Kf2 (48. Nf4 Bxf4 49. gxf4 $19) 48... Kg5 49. Kg2 { If I had this position again, I'd play a5 - locking down the pawns from ever pushing. Earlier, I was worried about the knight somehow attacking my weakened b6 pawn. But now, the knight is too under lock and key for that to ever happen. } 49... h4 50. gxh4+ Kxh4 51. b4 f4 52. Ng1 Bd6 53. b5 Bc5 { White cannot allow the king and pawn endgame to occur, so he tries for something else. } 54. Nf3+ exf3+ 55. Kxf3 Kxh3 56. Kxf4 Kg2 57. Ke5 Kf3 58. Kd5 Ke3 59. Kc6 Kd4 60. Kb7 Kxc4 { White resigned rather than get a new scorecard to cover this obviously winning endgame. } { [%cal Gb6b1] } 0-1


