1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. Nf3 Nc6 6. Bf4 { [%cal Gc8f5,Gd1b3,Gb3b7,Gb3d5] } 6... e6 7. e3 Bd6 8. Bg3 O-O 9. Bd3 Re8 (9... Qe7!?) 10. Ne5 { Stopping e5 from black } 10... Bxe5 11. dxe5 { [%cal Gf6e4] } 11... Nd7 12. f4 Qb6 { [%cal Gb6b2,Gb6e3] } 13. O-O! { [%cal Gd3h7,Gd1h5] } 13... Qxe3+?? { Taking a pawn with check ends up being a game losing blunder! The london attack is simply too strong. } (13... Nc5 14. Bc2 Qxb2 15. Qd2 Qb6 16. Rab1 Qd8 { A better pawn grab. } { [%cal Gc8f5] }) 14. Kh1 Qb6 15. Qh5 Nf8 { [%cal Gd7f8] } 16. Rf3 { [%csl Ge8][%cal Gg3f2,Gc6d4] } 16... Ng6 { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gf4f5] } (16... f5 { The move you "want" to make hangs a rook } 17. Qxe8) 17. Bf2 (17. f5 exf5 { [%cal Gd3f5,Gc8f5] } (17... Ngxe5 { [%cal Gf5f6,Ge5d3] } 18. fxe6 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gh5h7] } (18. f6 { [%cal Ge5g6] } 18... Nxd3 19. Qg5 { [%cal Gg5g7] } 19... g6 20. Qh6))) 17... Qd8 18. Nb5 { [%cal Gb5d6] } 18... Nce7 19. Nd6 { [%cal Gd6e8,Gd6f7] } 19... Bd7 20. Bh4 { [%cal Gf3h3,Ge7f5,Gg6h4] } 20... Qb6 21. Rh3 { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gf3h3,Gh3h7] } 21... h6 22. Bf6 Qxb2 (22... gxf6 23. Qxh6 { [%cal Gh6h7,Gh7f7] } 23... Nf8 (23... Rf8 24. Qh7#) 24. Qh8#) 23. Rf1 Nf5 24. Bxf5 { 1-0 Black resigns. } 24... exf5 25. Bxg7 Kxg7 26. Qxh6+ Kg8 27. Qh7+ Kf8 28. Qxf7# 1-0


