{ Part II: Attack and defense

Now that we have acquired terminology to explain chess fundamentals, we can apply this understanding to tackle larger chess concepts. In particular, the next four chapters will pick apart the basics of how to attack and defend in chess.

These chapters will be more difficult than the previous chapters because Morphy and his opponents will be playing higher level chess. As we leave behind miniatures caused by opening catastrophes, we will begin discussing middlegame strategy too. I firmly believe that anyone who has played through the first three chapters of this study can handle the increased complexity of these games too. }
 *


