5] }) 29. Qe7! Nc6 30. Qf6+ Kg8 31. Rd1 $18 { [%cal Gg2d5] }) 28... Rbc8?! (28... Qa6+ 29. Kg1 Qe6! { [%cal Gd7b8,Gd7c5,Gd8d2,Gc5e6,Gd2b2] } 30. Nc5 Qb6 (30... Qe7 31. Qc3 Rdc8) (30... Rxd2 31. Nxe6 Rxb2 { [%cal Gb4d3,Gd3f2] })) 29. Kg1 Qc5 30. Bh3 (30. Nxc5 Rxd2 31. Ne4 Rxb2 $19) 30... Qe7 31. Qe2 Rxd7 32. Bxd7 Qxd7 33. Qxe5+ Kg8 { Black is up a piece, but must avoid exchanging queenside pawns, needs to find shelter for his king, an dbring his knight to the kingside to target the f2 pawn. } 34. Qe4 a5 35. h4 { [%cal Gh4h5] } 35... Qd5 36. Qg4 Rf8 37. Rd1 Qf3 38. Qc4+ Qf7 39. Qc5 Qf5 40. Qc4+ Qf7 41. Qc5 Qf5 42. Qc4+ Kg7 { [%cal Gb4c6,Gc6e5,Ge5g4,Gg4f2] } 43. Qd4+ Qf6 44. Qc5 Rf7 { [%cal Gf6f2] } 45. Rd2 Qe7 { [%cal Gc5a5,Ge7e1,Ge1d2] } 46. Qc3+ Rf6 47. Rd4 Nc6 48. Rd5 (48. Rf4 Qe5 49. Rxf6 Qxc3 50. Rxg6+ Kxg6 51. bxc3 { But this ending is lost anyway } 51... Ne5 52. Kf1 Kf5 53. Ke2 Ke4 54. h5 h6 { Zug }) 48... Qe6 49. Rc5 h5 50. b3 Kf7 51. Rb5 Qd7 52. Kg2 Qe7 53. Qc4+ Kg7 54. Qd3 Kh6 55. Rd5 Rf7 56. Rd6 Ne5 { [%cal Ge5g4,Gg4f2] } 57. Qe3+ Kh7 58. Rb6?? (58. Rd5 Rf5 59. Rxa5 (59. f3!! { The only way to stop any progress from black - deny the g4 square from the knight. }) 59... Qb7+ 60. f3 (60. Kh3 Qh1#) (60. Kh2 Nf3+ 61. Kg2 Nxh4+) 60... Nc4) 58... Qc7! { With Ng4 coming, black is completely winning. So white resigned, rather than allow the attack to continue unabated. } { [%cal Ge5g4] } (58... Ng4? 59. Qxe7 Rxe7 60. b4 { Some drawing chances for white }) 59. Rb5 (59. f3 Rxf3 $19) (59. Qe4) 59... Ng4 $19 0-1


