1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. Nf3 b6 7. O-O Bb7 8. a3 Bxc3 9. bxc3 dxc4 10. Bxc4 c5 11. Bd3 Nbd7 (11... Qc7! 12. Re1 Be4 13. Bf1 Nc6 14. Nd2 Bg6 $10) 12. Re1 { [%cal Ge3e4] } 12... Ne4 13. Bb2 Rc8 (13... f5 14. c4 Rf6 15. a4 Rg6 16. a5 bxa5 $10 { Black has a terrible pawn structure, but potential for a kingside attack while white's pieces get misplaced going after the queenside pawns. }) 14. c4 { [%cal Gc8c7,Gd8a8,Gf8c8] } 14... Ndf6?! (14... Rc7 15. Qe2 Qa8 16. a4 Rfc8 { White retains an advantage here too. }) (14... f5 15. a4 Rf6 16. a5 $14) (14... cxd4? 15. exd4 { [%csl Ge4] }) 15. Ne5 Rc7 16. a4 Nd6 17. a5 Nd7 { This shows how much groveling black needs to do already in this position. } 18. axb6 axb6 19. Qh5 g6! (19... h6 20. Ng4 { [%cal Gg4h6,Gh5h6] } 20... Qg5! { Probably best defense. }) (19... f5 { [%cal Gf7f6] }) (19... Be4 20. Nxd7 Qxd7 21. Bxe4 Nxe4 22. Rad1 { [%cal Gd1d7] }) 20. Qh6 Nxe5 21. dxe5 Ne4 { If the bishop moves anywhere, then Qd2 comes and the e5 pawn is actually in the way of the b2 bishop. } 22. Bxe4! Bxe4 23. Red1 Rd7 (23... Bd3 24. Ra3 Rd7 $10) 24. Rd6! { Utilizing the power of the dark squared bishop again! } 24... Bb7 (24... f6? 25. exf6 { [%cal Gh6g7] } 25... Rff7 26. Rxd7 Rxd7 27. h4 $18 { [%cal Gh4h5,Gb2h8,Gh6g7] }) 25. Rad1?! (25. h4 { White gains a tempo by getting on with the attack. exd6 is always the plan, with or without the rook supporting it. } { [%cal Gh4h5] }) 25... Rxd6 26. exd6 f6 27. d7 Bc6 (27... Rf7 28. Qh3! f5 29. Qh6 Rxd7 30. Qg7+!! Rxg7 31. Rxd8+ Kf7 32. Bxg7 $18) (27... e5 28. h3 (28. f4 Rf7) 28... Rf7 29. Qh4! { Necessary to retain the advantage. Black cannot take on d7 without losing f6 and the long diagonal. }) 28. h4 Bxd7 29. h5 gxh5 (29... g5 30. Bxf6 Rxf6 31. Qxg5+ Kf7 32. h6 Ke7! { Black can barely survive this, but finding Ke7 as the only move is not easy... }) 30. e4 { [%cal Gd1d3,Gd3g3] } 30... e5 { [%cal Gd7g4] } 31. f4 exf4 (31... Rf7!! { Necessary to avoid complete disaster. } 32. fxe5 fxe5 { [%cal Gh6h5,Gd1d6] } 33. Qxh5 Qe8!! { [%cal Ge8e5,Gf7f1] } 34. Rd6?? (34. Qh6 Qe6 { Black continues to hold on with a sequence of only-moves. }) 34... Rf1+ $19) (31... Qe7 32. fxe5 fxe5 33. Bxe5 Qxe5 34. Rxd7 $18) 32. Rd6 Qe8 33. Bxf6 Rf7 (33... Qg6 34. Qxg6+ hxg6 35. Be7 Be8 36. Bxf8 Kxf8 37. Rxb6 { Losing the exchange and the game. }) 34. Rd5 $18 { Black resigned } { [%cal Gd5g5] } 1-0


