 after Nd8 } { [%cal Gf4g6,Gg6e7,Ge7g6] }) 25... Qe4 26. Rg1 Rg8 27. Ng3 Qxc4+ 28. Kg2 $15) 24. Nce2 Rg8 25. h5 Rg5 26. Ng3 Rxg3 $7 (26... Qg4 27. Bf3 $18) 27. fxg3 Rxe3 (27... Na5 28. Bxb7 Nxb7 { Still fine here, even though black's knight is completely offsides because as least white's pieces still aren't infiltrating. }) 28. Kf2 Re8 29. Re1! { [%cal Gf5f8,Gf4g6] } 29... Rxe1 (29... Rf8 30. Kg2 { [%cal Gf4g6] } 30... Kg7 31. Ng6 Qf2+ 32. Kh3 Qf5+ 33. g4 { [%cal Gf5f2] } 33... Qf2 34. Nxf8 Qxf8 35. Rf1 $18 { [%csl Gc6,Gb7][%cal Gf1f7] }) 30. Qxe1 { Black's queen is simply paralyzed by the dominant white minor pieces. Black's queenside pieces remain offsides as well. White has a crushing initiative. } 30... Kg7 31. Qe8 Qc2+ 32. Kg1 Qd1+ 33. Kh2 Qc2+ 34. Ng2 Qf5 35. Qg8+ Kf6 36. Qh8+ Kg5 37. Qg7+ $18 { Black resigned with forced mate coming. } { [%cal Gg5h5,Gg2f4] } 37... Kxh5 38. Bf7+ Qxf7 39. g4# 1-0


