1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 d6 6. Bg5 e6 7. Qd2 Be7 8. O-O-O Nxd4 9. Qxd4 O-O 10. f4 h6 11. Bh4 Qa5 12. e5 dxe5 13. Qxe5 b6!? (13... Qb6 14. Na4 Qc6 15. Bb5 Qxg2 16. Rhg1) (13... Qxe5 14. fxe5 Nd5 15. Bxe7 Nxe7 16. Bd3 { [%cal Gc8d7] } 16... Nc6 (16... b6!? 17. Be4 Rb8 18. Rhe1 Bb7 { Black should be getting his draw here }) 17. Rhe1 $14 { White establishes a bind }) 14. Qxa5 bxa5 { [%csl Gc2][%cal Gc2c8] } 15. Bd3 Bb7 16. Rhg1 Rfe8 (16... Bc5 17. Rge1 Bxg2? (17... Nd5 18. Nxd5 Bxd5 19. Be4 Bxe4 20. Rxe4 $16 { [%csl Gd8][%cal Gh4d8] }) 18. Bxf6 gxf6 19. Rg1 Bxg1 20. Rxg1 { [%cal Gg1g8] }) 17. h3 Bc5 18. Rge1 { [%cal Ge7c5,Gc5b4,Gb4c5] } 18... Bb4 (18... Kh8!? { Preparing to take on g2 potentially? }) 19. f5 { [%cal Gb4c3,Gb2c3] } 19... e5?! (19... Bxc3 20. bxc3 { Probably good for white as the c2 pawn protects the king and the c3 pawn can potentially run for a touchdown. }) (19... exf5 20. Bxf6 gxf6 21. Bxf5 Kf8 { Tough position, but apparently this is equal... } { [%cal Gb7g2] } 22. g4 Bf3 23. Rxe8+ Rxe8 24. Rd3 Re1+ 25. Kd2 Re2+ 26. Kd1 Re3+ 27. Kc1 { Weird repetition. }) 20. Bb5 Re7 21. Re3 a6 22. Ba4 Bc5 { [%cal Gb4c5] } 23. Re2 e4 24. Bb3 Rae8 25. Bxf6 gxf6 26. Bd5 e3 27. Bxb7 Rxb7 28. Rd5 Bb4 29. Rd3 Bxc3 30. Rxc3 Rbe7 31. Rd3 Re4! { Stopping c4, followed by Rc3 where white is nearly winning. } 32. c3 Kg7 33. Kc2 R4e5 { [%csl Gg2,Gg4] } 34. g4?! (34. g3! Rxf5 35. Rdxe3 Rxe3 36. Rxe3 a4 37. c4 Rf2+ 38. Kc3 a3 39. bxa3 Rxa2 40. Kb4 { White has winning chances here due to his passed c pawn far away from black's king. } { [%cal Gc4c8] }) 34... h5 35. Rd6 { [%cal Gd6f6] } (35. Rd4 hxg4 36. hxg4 Kh6 37. Kd3 Kg5 38. Rh2!! { Unstoppable mate means that this line, overlooked by Bronstein and the players, is equally winning for white. } { [%cal Gh2h5] }) 35... hxg4 36. hxg4 Kh6!? 37. Rxf6+ Kg5 38. Rxf7 Kxg4 39. Rd7 Kf3 40. Kd3 Rxf5 41. c4 a4 42. Rd6 $10 { Draw agreed after adjournament. } { [%csl Gc4,Ge2][%cal Gd6d7,Gd7d6,Gd3e2,Gd3c4] } (42. c5?? Re