[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/NoseKnowsAll"]
[UTCDate "2021.05.14"]
[UTCTime "22:53:48"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 Nbd7 7. f4?! { More analysis on showing why I don't believe in this move. } 7... e5 (7... Qc7 8. Qf3 h6 9. Bxf6 Nxf6 10. f5!) (7... h6 8. Bxf6 Nxf6) (7... Qb6 8. Qd2 Qxb2? { This move order is inaccurate, because black will not get in e5 now. } (8... e5 { Transposes to the mainline }) 9. Rb1 Qa3 10. Bxf6! Nxf6 11. e5 dxe5 12. fxe5 Nd7?? (12... Ng4 13. Nd5 Qc5 14. Nb3 Qc6 15. Qa5 b6 16. Nd4! $16 { [%cal Gd5c7] }) 13. Nd5! { Black cannot prevent Nc7+ now } { [%csl Gc7] } 13... Qc5 14. Nb3 Qc6 15. Na5 Qc5 16. Nxb7 Bxb7 17. Rxb7 Rc8 18. Bxa6 $18) 8. Nf5 Qb6 { A rare poisoned pawn variation, but one that is a serious try for black. The knight on f5 is temporarily good, but can get kicked back at any point if white plays inaccurately. } 9. Qd2 Qxb2 10. Rb1 Qa3 11. Be2 h6 (11... exf4 12. Bxf4 Ne5 13. Rb3 Qc5 14. Be3 Qc6 15. Rb6 Qc7 16. O-O (16. Nxd6+!? Bxd6 17. Rxd6 Be6 18. Bb6 Qe7 19. O-O O-O 20. Rd1 $10) 16... Bxf5 17. exf5 d5!? 18. Rxf6 gxf6 19. Nxd5 O-O-O 20. Nxc7 Rxd2 21. Bxd2 Bc5+ 22. Kh1 Kxc7 { White has the bishop pair and a slightly better pawn structure, and can hopefully massage a win here. }) 12. Bh4 exf4 13. O-O { [%csl Gf4][%cal Gf1f4] } 13... g6 14. Rxf4 g5! (14... gxf5?? 15. Rxf5 b5 16. Rb3 Qa5 17. Qf4 { Black's queen is a lot more misplaced on a5 than on the usual square: c5 } { [%cal Gf5f6] }) 15. Rb3 Qa5 16. Nxd6+ Bxd6 17. Qxd6 gxf4 18. Ra3 Qb6+ 19. Qxb6 Nxb6 20. Bxf6 Rg8 21. Rb3 Nd7 22. Nd5 { While this forced line is technically equal, white has a lot of compensation for the exchange, and black is still under the gun for a while unless they give back the exchange soon. With best play, this should definitely be a draw though... } *


