1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Be7 8. Qf3 h6 9. Bh4 Nbd7 10. O-O-O Qc7 11. Be2 Rg8? { Honestly, a mistake, bore out by years of theory and modern engines. White can play similarly to the Rb8 line, but things are even better here... } 12. Rhf1 g5 13. Bg3! (13. fxg5 Ne5 14. Qe3 hxg5 15. Bg3 { Also good, but black has their share of play. }) 13... gxf4 (13... b5!? 14. e5 Bb7 15. Qd3 dxe5 (15... Nc5!? 16. Qe3 dxe5 17. fxe5 Nd5 18. Nxd5 Bxd5 19. Bf3 O-O-O 20. Bxd5 Rxd5 21. Rxf7 $18) 16. Nxe6!! fxe6 17. fxe5 Nd5 (17... Nxe5?? 18. Bxe5 Qxe5 19. Bh5+! Kf8 (19... Nxh5?? 20. Qd7#) 20. Qh7 Rg7 21. Qh8+ Rg8 22. Qxh6+ Rg7 23. Rde1 { [%cal Gf1f6] } 23... Qd4 24. Ne4! Bxe4 25. Rxe4 Qxe4 26. Qh8+ Rg8 27. Rxf6+ Bxf6 28. Qxf6#) 18. Qh7 O-O-O { Black has to abandon the bishop or get killed in the center. } (18... Nxc3?? 19. Qxg8+ Bf8 20. Qf7+ Kd8 21. Qxf8# { [%cal Gd1d8] }) (18... Rf8?? 19. Qg6+ Kd8 20. Qxe6 Rxf1 21. Rxf1 $18 Nxc3?? 22. Qg8+ Bf8 23. Rxf8+ Nxf8 24. Qxf8+ Kd7 25. Bg4+ Kc6 26. Qf6+ Kc5 27. bxc3 $18 { [%cal Gg3f2] }) 19. Nxd5 Bxd5 20. Qxe7 $16) 14. Qxf4 $16 { White avoids Ne5 gaining a tempo on the queen and therefore has a terrific attack. Black has to bail out with only losing a pawn or get completely steamrolled. } 14... Qc5 (14... Ne5? 15. Qxh6 Rg6 16. Qh8+ Rg8 17. Qh4 Ng6 18. Qh6 Rh8 19. Qe3 $18 { Nb5 is the threat - breaking through to d6 and the black king. }) (14... e5?! 15. Nd5! Nxd5?? (15... exf4 16. Nxc7+ Kd8 17. Nxa8 fxg3 18. h4 $18 { Our knight on a8 is getting out. }) 16. Qxf7+ Kd8 17. Ne6#) 15. Qxh6 Qg5+ 16. Qxg5 Rxg5 $16 *


