1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 b5 { Black doesn't stop e5? We play it. } 8. e5 dxe5 9. fxe5 Qc7! { The point of the opening: Black goes for Qe5+ to win our undefended g5 bishop } (9... h6? 10. Bh4 g5 11. exf6 gxh4 12. Qf3! $18 { [%cal Gf3a8] }) 10. exf6 Qe5+ 11. Be2 Qxg5 12. O-O Ra7! { An odd, but only move! Avoids Bf3 with tempo. } (12... Bb7?? 13. Bf3 Qe3+ 14. Kh1 Bxf3 15. Rxf3 Qe5 16. Nxe6! fxe6 (16... Qxe6? 17. Nd5 $18 { [%cal Gd5c7,Gf3e3] }) 17. f7+ Ke7 18. Qf1!! { Getting out of the way of the other rook coming to the important e file, and avoids a potential loss of tempo with Rd8. } 18... Nd7 19. Re1 Qc5 20. Rfe3 e5 21. Qf5 $18 { [%cal Ge3e5] }) (12... Bd6?? 13. Nxe6 $18 { [%cal Gd1d6] } 13... Qe3+ (13... Qe5!? 14. Nxg7+ Kf8 15. g3 $18) 14. Kh1 Qxe6 15. fxg7 Rg8 16. Re1 $18 { [%cal Re1e8] }) (12... Nd7?? 13. Bf3! Ra7 14. Bc6 Bc5 15. Ne4 Qe3+ 16. Kh1 Qxd4 17. fxg7! Qxg7 (17... Rg8? 18. Nf6+ Kd8 19. Qxd4 Bxd4 20. Nxg8 $18) 18. Nxc5 Qe5 19. Nd3 $18) (12... Qe5?? 13. Kh1! Ra7 14. Nf3 Qxf6 15. a4 Bc5 (15... b4?? 16. Ne4 Qg6 17. Nd6+ Bxd6 18. Qxd6 { [%csl Gb8] } 18... Nd7 19. Rad1 $18) 16. Ne4 Qe7 17. Nxc5 Qxc5 18. axb5 O-O (18... axb5?? 19. Rxa7 Qxa7 20. Qd6! $18 { [%cal Rd6b8,Bd6f8] }) 19. Qd4 Qxd4 20. Nxd4 Rd7 21. Nc6 Nxc6 22. bxc6 Rd6 23. Bf3 $16 { White is up a solid connected passed pawn and should go on to win this }) (12... Qe3+? { Inserting this check and trying to get back to main lines is a recipe for disaster: } 13. Kh1 Ra7?? 14. Nf5! exf5 15. Bxb5+ axb5 16. Re1 $18) 13. Qd3 Rd7 14. Ne4 Qe5 (14... Qd5? 15. c3 e5 16. fxg7 Bxg7 17. Qg3 $18) (14... Qg6?! 15. Bf3 Bb7 (15... e5? 16. Qc3 { [%cal Gc3c8] } 16... Bb7 17. Rae1 $18) 16. Qc3! Bxe4 17. Rae1! { Preparing Qc8+ and Rxe6+, crushing. } 17... Bxf3?? 18. Qc8+ Rd8 19. Rxe6+ fxe6 20. Qxe6+ Be7 21. Qxe7#) 15. Nf3! Rxd3 (15... Qxb2? 16. Qe3 Bb7 17. Rab1 Qxc2!? (17... Qxa2!? 18. Kh1 Bxe4 19. Qxe4 Qd5 20. Qf4 { [%cal Gf4b8] } 20... Bd6 21. fxg7! Rg8 22. Qh6 Qf5 23. Bd3 { [%cal Gd3h7] } 23... Bf4! 24. Qh4 Rxd3 25. cxd3 Rxg7 26. Rfc1! Bxc1 27. Rxc1 $18 { [%cal Gc1c8,Gc1c7] }) 18. Nfg5 Qc7 19. a4 b4 20. Rxb4!! Bxb4 21. fxg7 Rg8 22. Nf6+ Kd8 23. Nxg8 $18 Bc5?? 24. Nxe6+!! fxe6 25. Rf8+ Bxf8 26. gxf8=Q#) (15... Qc7!? { The other alternative trades queens and leaves black with a sad endgame: } 16. Qe3 Qa7 (16... Bb7?! { The last try for a "game," but white is better after the simple } 17. a4 b4 18. Kh1 $14 { After which all of the thematic moves (Rae1, Nfg5, fxg7) start to become threats. }) 17. Qxa7 Rxa7 18. a4 $14) 16. Nxe5 Rd4 (16... Re3? 17. fxg7! Bxg7 18. Nd6+ Ke7 19. Nxc8+ Rxc8 20. Rxf7+ Kd6 21. Rxg7 $16) 17. fxg7 Bxg7 18. Nxf7 O-O! (18... Rf8? 19. c3! $16) (18... Rxe4?? 19. Nd6+ $18) 19. Nfg5 Rxf1+ (19... h6?! 20. Rxf8+ Kxf8 21. c3 Ra4 22. Nd6 $16 { [%cal Rd6c8] }) 20. Kxf1! (20. Rxf1?! h6 21. c3 Ra4 { Black has a tempo to attack our undefended a pawn }) 20... h6 21. c3 Ra4 22. Nd6 hxg5 (22... Bd7 23. Nge4 Bc6 24. Bf3 Nd7 25. a3 $14) 23. Nxc8 Rf4+ 24. Kg1 $14 { White must avoid trading down into an opposite color bishop ending, but otherwise could have enough to win this one. } *


