1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Be7 8. Qf3 Qc7 9. O-O-O Nbd7 10. g4 b5 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. g5 Nd7 13. f5! { We enter the absolute main line of the Bg5 Najdorf. White sacrifices the g pawn in order to speed up an attack on black's king/kingside. Black is usually hesitant to castle kingside directly into white's attack, but recent engines show that this move is quite playable.
White quickly gets on with the attack before the queenside pawn storm rolls them. } 13... O-O!? { Modern engines believe this is Black's best try. Indeed, black gets a lot of play in the center and queenside too. } 14. Rg1 b4 15. Nce2 e5 (15... Bb7 16. f6! $18) 16. f6 exd4 (16... Bd8?? 17. fxg7 Kxg7 18. Nf5+ $18) 17. fxe7 Re8 18. Nxd4 Ne5 { Black retains the e5 outpost for their knight. But white already has open lines towards black's king, and a further h4-h5-h6 will soften the dark squares or a g6 move to soften up the light squares. } (18... g6? 19. Nf5! { Threatening Nh6+ } 19... gxf5 (19... Ne5?? 20. Nh6+ Kg7 21. Qf6#) 20. exf5 { [%csl Ga8] } 20... Bb7 21. Qe3 Rac8 22. Rd2 { Cañamas Soler, José Vicente - Gómez-Galán Arense, Joaquín, 1-0, ESP/W/C/023 (ESP), 2015, https://lichess.org/YnXcMbrl } 22... Ne5 (22... Qa5?? { An interesting try that falls flat beautifully: } 23. g6!! Qxa2 24. gxf7+ Kxf7 25. Rxd6 $18 { [%cal Ge3e6] }) 23. f6 $16 Qa5 24. g6!! { The same important move. } 24... fxg6 25. Qb3+ d5 26. Bh3 Rc6 { And finally the attack can play itself out. } 27. Re2 Nf7?? 28. Bd7 $18) 19. Qf4 Be6 (19... Rxe7!? 20. Nf5 Bxf5 21. exf5 $14 { Kosintseva, Tatiana - Ju, Wenjun, 1/2-1/2, Nalchik FIDE GP (Women), 2011, https://lichess.org/UwecCNcX }) 20. Nxe6 (20. Nf5!?) 20... fxe6 21. Rg3 (21. h4?! { Too early, the undefended rook on g1 will end up with black gaining a tempo anyway } 21... Rxe7 22. h5? Qc5 { [%cal Gc5g1] } 23. Rg3 Rc7 24. Rd2?? Rf8! $19) 21... Rab8 (21... Rac8 22. Qd2 $14) (21... Rxe7 22. Qd2 $14) 22. h4 Qxe7 (22... Rxe7 23. Qd2! { [%csl Gd6][%cal Gd2d6] } 23... Rb6 (23... Rc8? 24. Bxa6 Ra8 25. Qxd6 $16) 24. h5 $14) 23. h5 Rf8 24. Qe3 $14 { Grobler, David J. - Franks, Keith, 1-0, ENG/Chp2/SFA (ENG), 2019, https://lichess.org/nHH5jmH4 } *


