1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Be7 8. Qf3 Qc7 9. O-O-O Nbd7 10. g4 b5 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. g5 Nd7 13. f5 Bxg5+ 14. Kb1 Ne5 (14... O-O 15. fxe6 Nb6 (15... fxe6? 16. Qg3 { [%cal Gg3g5,Gd4e6] } 16... Bf6 17. Nxe6 $18) (15... Ne5 16. Qg3 Qd8 (16... Bf6? 17. Nd5 Qd8 18. Bh3 $16) 17. h4 Bf6 18. Bh3 $16 { A clear improvement over the 15. Qh5 lines. The queen is better placed on g3. }) 16. Nd5 Nxd5 17. exd5 fxe6 18. Qg4 { [%cal Gg4g5,Gd4e6] } 18... e5 19. Qxg5 exd4 20. Bd3 g6 $16) (14... Bf6? 15. fxe6 fxe6?? (15... Ne5 16. Nd5! Nxf3 17. Nxc7+ Kd8 18. Nxa8 $18) 16. Nxe6 $18) 15. Qh5! { Pins the f pawn and gains a tempo against the g5 bishop. Note the priyome: g6 is not a threat as long as exf7+ must be met with Kxf7 or Nxf7. } 15... h6 (15... Qd8?! { The most common move for black doesn't seem that inspiring. White has open lines everywhere. } 16. h4 Bf6 17. fxe6 O-O 18. Bh3! fxe6 19. Bxe6+ Kh8 20. Nd5 $16) (15... Qe7?! 16. Nxe6 Bxe6 17. fxe6 O-O (17... g6?! 18. exf7+ Kxf7 (18... Qxf7?? 19. Qxg5 $18) 19. Qh3 $16) 18. Nd5! Qd8 19. h4 Bf6 20. Bh3 $16 { With play quite similar to the other line, white should also be better here too. }) (15... Bf6 16. Nxe6 Bxe6 17. fxe6 O-O (17... g6?! 18. Nd5! Qd8 19. exf7+ Kxf7 20. Qh3 $16) 18. Nd5 Qd8 19. Bh3 $14 { At least here, white has blocked their h pawn, so black can claim some sort of improvement over the other lines... }) 16. Nxe6 Bxe6 17. fxe6 g6 18. exf7+ (18. Nd5?! Qxc2+! { The reason the usual priyome doesn't work. Black's bishop is actually defended for once. } 19. Kxc2 Rc8+ 20. Kb1 gxh5 21. exf7+ Kxf7 22. h4 Be7 $14) 18... Qxf7 19. Qh3 $14 { While black has full control over the e5 outpost, white has full control over the (slightly more important) d5 outpost. White can hope to poke the g5 bishop with h4 and break through to the weakened king, but must also reckon with the eventual b4-b3 push. A sample line goes: } 19... Rd8 20. Be2 O-O 21. Rhf1 Qg7 22. Rxf8+ Qxf8 23. Qg3 $14 { As long as we don't trade queens, but white could be better here. Play continues. } { [%cal Gc3d5] } *


