1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 h6 8. Bh4 Qb6 (8... Be7 9. Qf3 Nbd7 10. O-O-O Qc7 { Transposes to the Browne variation }) 9. a3 Be7 (9... Nbd7 10. Bf2 Qc7 11. Qf3 { Can transpose to the main line here, but black has the extra option of playing b5 first: } 11... b5 (11... Be7 { Transposing... }) 12. O-O-O Bb7 13. Bd3! (13. g4?! d5! $10 { Black has extra support for the d5 pawn break (and e4 square) in this line. } 14. e5 Ne4) 13... Be7 { This line has more in common with the Anand variation than the delayed poisoned pawn. } 14. Rhe1!? { Similar play to the Anand variation } (14. g4!? { Similar play as to the main line, but admittedly this is a move order that should be explored further })) (9... Qxb2?? 10. Na4 $18 { The point of a3: Black cannot take on b2. }) 10. Bf2 Qc7 11. Qf3 { This position is identical to the main line, except white has inserted a3 and retreated the bishop to f2. } 11... Nbd7 (11... b5 12. g4 Bb7? (12... Nbd7 13. O-O-O { Black would do well here to transpose back to the main line again. }) 13. g5 hxg5 14. fxg5 Nh5 15. g6! $16 { [%csl Gf7,Ge6] }) 12. O-O-O b5 13. g4 Bb7 14. Bg2 O-O { Never been tried before, but a reasonable move overall... } 15. h4 d5 (15... b4?! 16. axb4 a5 17. b5 a4 18. g5 a3 19. b3 hxg5 20. hxg5 Ne8 21. Qh5 $18 { If black doesn't destabilize the center quickly, white's attack rolls over black }) 16. e5 Ne4 17. Be1 b4?! (17... Rfc8 18. Rh3 b4? { A worse version of the other line. } (18... Qb6 19. g5 $16) 19. axb4 a5 20. b5 a4 21. Kb1) 18. axb4 a5 19. b5 a4 20. Kb1 a3 21. b3 Rfc8 22. Rh3 Qb6 23. Ka2 Bb4 24. Nxe4 dxe4 (24... Bxe1 25. Qe3 { Better to avoid letting the queen in to the weakened dark squares than to recapture. } 25... Bb4 26. Nd6 Bxd6 27. exd6 Qxd6 28. Rg3 $18) 25. Qe3 Bxe1 26. Rxe1 Nc5 27. g5 h5 28. g6 fxg6 29. Rg3 Kh7 30. Rg1 Na4 31. Rxg6 $18 { The key to this attack is not to rush it. If black all-ins on the queenside, white can first ensure the center and queenside are safe before launching the true, decisive attack against the naked black king. } 31... Rc3?? 32. Bxe4 Rxe3 33. Rxg7+ Kh8 34. Rh7# *


