1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Qb6 { Sadly, I've not found a refutation to the poisoned pawn variation. With best play in this line, black should still be fine. But it's devilishly tricky for black throughout, so this line is at least something worthwhile to try. } 8. Qd3!? { A sideline, but one that has many tricks based on the fact that the queen on a3 may run into Nd5 discovered attacks throughout. } 8... Qxb2 9. Rb1 Qa3 10. f5 (10. Be2!? { I can't tell exactly how strong this sideline is for white, but you do get your king castled, and black needs to play extremely precisely to keep any edge in it: } 10... Nbd7 11. O-O Be7 12. Kh1 { Adhiban, Baskaran - Wei Yi, 1-0, IND-CHN Summit 2015, https://lichess.org/Wqr26Pw3 } 12... Qc5 { This move might just be the improvement though that Wei Yi needed to find to keep a safe advantage. Black will castle next. } 13. Rbd1 O-O 14. Qg3 $13) 10... Be7 (10... e5?! 11. Bxf6 gxf6 12. Nb3 $14 { White will have the d5 square for eternity. }) (10... Qc5!? { Xmask's idea to try something different as black. } 11. Be3 Qc7 (11... Ng4? 12. Nxe6! Qxe3+ 13. Qxe3 Nxe3 14. Nc7+ Kd8 15. Nxa8 $16) 12. fxe6 Bxe6! { The only good recapture. } (12... fxe6?! 13. Be2 Be7 14. O-O O-O 15. Qc4 $14) 13. Nxe6 fxe6 14. Qc4 Qd7 15. Qb3 $10 { This usual regrouping, avoiding d5 and targeting the b pawn keeps the game level. Unfortunately, white will only be equal in the endgame - not better. }) 11. fxe6 fxe6 (11... Bxe6!? 12. Rxb7 Qc5 13. Nd5! Bxd5 14. exd5 Qxd5?? (14... Nxd5? 15. Qe4 $18 { Threatening Rxe7+ Nxe7, Qxa8 }) (14... h6! 15. Qe3 Qa5+ 16. Kd1 O-O $10 { Morokova, Larisa Vasilievna - Hildebrand, Dieter, 1/2-1/2, CT20/pr34, 2013, https://lichess.org/CilVKwez }) 15. Rxe7+! $18) 12. Be2 O-O?! (12... e5? 13. Nf5 Bxf5 14. exf5 Nbd7 15. Rxb7 Rc8 16. Bd2 { White isn't even down a pawn anymore. The bishop pair will make itself felt. } 16... O-O 17. Nd5 Qxd3 18. Nxe7+ Kf7 19. cxd3 Kxe7 20. g4 $16) (12... Qc5! $10 13. Be3 Qa5 14. Bd2 $10 { Transposing to the Be7 chapter. }) 13. Nd5! { [%cal Gd3a3,Gd5e7] } 13... Qxd3 14. Nxe7+ Kf7 15. cxd3 Kxe7 16. O-O $14 { White has a stable center, the two bishops, a slight initiative, and a safe king. For instance as in this line: } 16... h6 17. Bc1! e5 18. Nf3 (18. Ba3!? { Unnecessary, but awesome! } 18... exd4 19. e5 $14) 18... Nc6 19. Ba3 b5 20. d4 b4 21. Bxb4 Nxb4 22. Rxb4 $14 *


