1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Qb6 8. Qd3 Qxb2 9. Rb1 Qa3 10. f5 Nc6?! { Not a bad move objectively, but it is asking for trouble in so many of the ensuing lines. } 11. fxe6 fxe6 (11... Nxd4?? 12. exf7+ Kxf7 13. Qxd4 $18) 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. Be2 Qa5! { Gaining a tempo on the undefended bishop is crucial. } (13... Be7? { Transposing to a bad line: see the next chapter }) (13... Qc5? 14. Be3 $16 { Black doesn't gain the tempo they wanted, and will soon run into the e5 break anyway.... }) 14. Bd2 Qc7?! { The main move seems extremely risky: } (14... Qd8!? { Engine recommendation stops e5 temporarily... } 15. Rd1 { [%cal Ge4e5] } 15... e5! 16. O-O Be6 17. Qg3 $10 { Possibly equal, but you can feel how difficult it is for black to untangle. }) (14... Be7!? 15. Nd5 { [%cal Gd2a5] } 15... Qd8 16. Nxe7 Qxe7 17. e5! dxe5 18. O-O O-O 19. Bg5 a5 $10 { White keeps the bishop pair, more active rooks, and chances for a perpetual check, but black has almost fully untangled, so should hold with best play. }) (14... Qe5? 15. O-O Be7 16. Bf4 Qc5+ 17. Kh1 O-O 18. Na4 $16 { Pressure on d6, b6 ensures that black is not simply out of the woods once they castle. } { Lu, Shanglei - Antipov, Mikhail Al, 1-0, Moscow Dvorkovich Cup U16 6th, 2011, https://lichess.org/PscVWanD }) 15. e5! dxe5 (15... Nd5 16. O-O Be7 17. exd6 Bxd6 18. Bh5+ g6 19. Nxd5 cxd5 20. Bxg6+ hxg6 21. Qxg6+ Kd8 (21... Kd7 22. Qg7+ $18) (21... Ke7 22. Qg7+ $18) 22. Qf6+ $18) 16. Ne4 Be7 (16... Nxe4? 17. Qxe4 Bc5 (17... Be7 18. O-O $18 { Now black cannot castle, and their king will be dead in the center. }) 18. Rf1 { [%cal Ge2h5] } 18... g6 19. h4 Rf8 20. Rxf8+ Kxf8 21. h5 $18 { Black simply can't move any pieces. As long as white keeps the queen and rook on the board, white should be winning. }) 17. Nxf6+ Bxf6 18. Bh5+! g6 19. O-O!! O-O (19... gxh5?? 20. Rxf6 $18) 20. Bxg6 hxg6 21. Bh6 { First we stop Qg7 before going in for the kill } 21... Bg7 22. Rxf8+ Kxf8 23. Rf1+ Kg8 24. Qxg6 Ra7 25. h4 { Betker, Jörg - Cardelli, Gabriel, 1-0, GER/Ma02 (GER), 2013, https://lichess.org/h7aFpiKN } 25... Qb6+ (25... Kh8?? 26. Bxg7+ Qxg7 27. Qh5+ Kg8 28. Qe8+ Kh7 29. Rf8 $18 { [%cal Ge8h5] }) (25... Qd8?? 26. Bg5! Qd4+ 27. Kh1 { There's nothing to do. The h pawn will decide the game. } 27... e4 28. h5 Kh8 29. h6 Bxh6 30. Qxh6+ Kg8 31. Rf8#) 26. Kh1 e4 (26... Qd4?? 27. Bg5!) 27. Qe8+ (27. Bg5? { Here, this typical bishop reroute is just not quite in time. } 27... e3! 28. h5 e2! { And white has to take the perpetual check or they are lost. }) 27... Kh7 28. Bxg7 Rxg7 29. Qxc8 $16 { With best play, black enters this dangerous endgame, where their unsafe king could quickly decide the game. } { [%cal Gf1f8] } *


