{ This is one of the hardest puzzles in this study, so don't feel bad if you can't find the all-important second move. Consider ALL forcing moves: checks, captures, and threats. }
1. Qd6+ Ka8 { If Kc8, then Qd8 immediately mates the black king } 2. Qc6!! (2. Nc6 { A good idea, but Rg8 defends any of the back-rank threats }) (2. Qc7?? { Good idea, but after Bxg2+! white is actually the one getting mated! } 2... Bxg2+) 2... Qc8 { Did you calculate how to mate the opponent if bxa5 or Bxc6 was played? } (2... bxa5 3. Rd8+ Qc8 4. Rxc8#) (2... Bxc6 3. Rd8+ Qc8 4. Rxc8#) 3. Rd8 Bxc6 { Did you see how to mate the opponent if Rg8 was played? } (3... Rg8 4. Qxb7#) 4. Rxc8# *


