1. Qxh7+ (1. Qh6+ { Yes this move also mates, but it's a little slower. } 1... Kh8 2. g7+ Kg8 3. Bxh7+ Nxh7 4. Qg6 { [%cal Gg4h6] }) 1... Nxh7 2. Rf7+ Kh8 3. g7+ (3. Nh6 { Yes this move also mates, with the threat of g7# and Rxh7#. Switch the move order for the solution. }) (3. Rxh7+ { This move also mates, but it's incredibly slow. }) 3... Kg8 4. Nh6# { While there are many mates in this position, it's important to recognize that sacrificing the queen is the key ingredient to opening up our own pieces, while simultaneously uncoordinating the defenders. } *


