[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

1. Qxh6+! (1. Nh5+?? { Tempting, but after gxh5 Rg3+ Kh7 there is no follow-up. } 1... gxh5 2. Rg3+ Kh7 3. Qe4+ Kh8 $16) 1... Kxh6 2. Rh3+ Kg5 { Did you see the checkmate if the king returns to g7? } (2... Kg7 3. Rh7#) 3. Rf1!! Qxe5 { Rf1 sealed the king in and there's no escape! On any other move, Ne4# would have been played. } 4. Nh7# { When black's king is so vulnerable and our king is completely safe, we can afford to play a forcing move that is not check but merely further closes the mating net. Rf1 was the crucial move of this mate, since black could no longer stop both Ne4# and Nh7#. } *


