{ This position was taken from an online blitz game between Supi and Carlsen in which the previous World Chess Champion played in an enterprising, but dubious manner. Can you finish off Magnus? }
1. Qc6! (1. Qxb7+ { No mate. The king can escape to the d file. } 1... Kxb7 2. Ra7+ Kc8 3. Ra8+ Kd7) 1... bxc6 2. bxc6 Qb5 3. cxb5 (3. Ra8+ { We're already down a queen, so we can't allow Magnus to block the check by sacrificing his queen back! } 3... Qb8) 3... Re8 { There's no longer a defense... } 4. Ra8# { Exactly! One of the rare positions where a pawn is just as valuable as a queen in checkmating the enemy king! } *


