{ The famous conclusion to the "Uruguayan Immortal" game. }
1... Bg1+! (1... Ng4+ { This move was not played in the game but still mates. Note that hxg4 Qh6+ does not mate due to Qh3! }) 2. Qxg1 { Excellent! Did you see how to mate if white had played Kxg1 instead? } (2. Kxg1 Qxg3+ 3. Qg2 Qxg2#) 2... Ng4+! 3. hxg4 Qh6+ 4. Bh4 Qxh4# { Beautiful! Bg1+ is both a deflection (of the queen from h3) and an attraction (of the queen to g1). } *


