{ Game 17 of the 1957 WCC match. Smyslov was up 1 point in the match at this point. }
1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. c4 c6 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. d4 O-O 6. Nc3 d5 7. cxd5 cxd5 8. Ne5 b6 9. Bg5 Bb7 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. O-O e6 12. f4 Bg7 13. Rc1 f6 14. Nf3 Nc6 15. e3 Qd7 16. Qe2 Na5 17. h4 Nc4 18. Bh3 Nd6 19. Kh2 a5 20. Rfe1 b5 21. Nd1 b4 22. Nf2 Ba6 23. Qd1 Rfc8 24. Rxc8+ Rxc8 25. Bf1 Bxf1 26. Rxf1 Qc6 27. Nd3 Qc2+ 28. Qxc2 Rxc2+ 29. Rf2 Rxf2+ 30. Nxf2 Nc4 31. Nd1 Kf7 32. b3 Nd6 33. Kg2 h5 34. Kh3 Ne4 35. g4 hxg4+ 36. Kxg4 f5+ 37. Kh3 Bf6 38. Ne1 Kg7 39. Nd3 Nc3 40. Nxc3 bxc3 41. Ne1 { This is the starting position in Silman's book.
Kh6 was the adjourned move. Apparently Botvinnik's second (Goldberg) sent an offer of a draw the following morning since the black king seemingly cannot cross a defensive line on the 3rd rank. But with zugzwang, all things are possible... } 41... Kh6 42. Nc2 Be7 43. Kg3?! { Not trading off the pawns means the game continues. } (43. a3! Kh5 44. b4 axb4 45. axb4 Bxh4 46. b5 Bd8 47. Kg3 g5 48. fxg5 Kxg5 49. Kf3 Bb6 50. Ne1 Kf6 51. Ke2 f4 52. Kd3! fxe3 53. Nc2! e5 54. Nxe3 Ke6 55. Nxd5! Kxd5 56. dxe5 Bd4 57. b6 $10 { Kasparov's analysis proving there was a draw. }) 43... Kh5 44. Kf3 Kxh4 45. Ne1?! (45. a4! g5 46. fxg5 Kxg5 47. Ke2! f4!? (47... Bd6!? 48. Kd3 f4 49. exf4+ Kxf4 50. Kxc3 Ke4 51. b4! axb4+ 52. Nxb4 Bxb4+?! 53. Kxb4 e5! (53... Kxd4?? 54. a5 e5 55. a6 e4 56. a7 e3 57. a8=Q $18) 54. dxe5 Kxe5 $10) 48. Kf3! $10) 45... g5 46. fxg5 Kxg5 47. Nc2 Bd6 48. Ne1 (48. a3?! Kh4 49. b4 a4! 50. b5 Bc7 51. Ne1 Kg5 52. Nc2 Ba5 53. Ne1 Bb6 54. Nc2 Kf6 $19 { "the pawns on the a file improve black's winning chances." }) 48... Kh4 49. Nc2 Kh3 50. Na1 Kh2! 51. Kf2 Bg3+ 52. Kf3!? (52. Kf1!? Bh4 53. Ke2 Kg2 $19) 52... Bh4 53. Nc2 Kg1 54. Ke2 Kg2 55. Na1 Be7 56. Nc2 Kg3 57. Ne1 Bd8 58. Nc2 Bf6 { Zugzwang. If the knight moves, f4 is decisive. Kd3 allows Kf2. } 59. a3!? (59. Kd3!? Kf2! 60. Na1!? (60. a3!? Be7 61. b4 a4 $19) (60. Kxc3!? Ke2 61. a3 e5 62. b4 exd4+ 63. exd4 Bd8! $19 { [%cal Gf5f1] }) 60... Ke1! 61. Nc2+ Kd1 62. Na1 Be7 63. Nc2 Bd6 64. Na1 Kc1 65. Kxc3 Bb4+ 66. Kd3 Kb2 67. Nc2 Kxa2! $19) 59... Be7 60. b4!? (60. a4!? Bd6 61. Ne1 e5 62. dxe5 Bxe5 63. Kd3!? (63. Nc2!? d4! 64. exd4 Bd6 65. Ne3 f4 66. Nf5+ Kg4 67. Nxd6 f3+ $19 { [%cal Gc3c1,Gf3f1] }) 63... d4! 64. exd4 Bd6 65. Nc2 (65. Kxc3?? Bb4+ $19) 65... f4 66. Kxc3 f3 67. Ne3 f2! 68. Kd3 Kf3 69. Nf1 Bf4! 70. d5 Kg2 71. Ke2 Kg1 $19 { Smyslov's line }) 60... a4! 61. Ne1 Bg5 62. Nc2 Bf6 { Zugzwang again. Any knight move allows f4. } 63. Kd3!? (63. b5!? Bd8 64. Ne1 Ba5 65. Nc2 Kg4 66. Ne1 Bc7 67. Nc2 Bb6 68. Nb4 f4 69. exf4 Bxd4 70. Kd3 Bb6 71. Kxc3 Kxf4 72. Nc6 Ke3 73. Kb4 d4 74. Ne5 d3 75. Kxa4 d2 76. Nc4+ Ke2 77. Nxd2 Kxd2 78. Kb4 e5 79. a4 e4 80. a5 Bd8 81. b6 e3 $19 { Smyslov's line }) 63... Kf2 64. Na1 Bd8 65. Nc2 Bg5 { Zugwang again! } 66. b5!? (66. Na1? Bxe3 $19) (66. Kxc3?! Ke2 67. b5 Bd8 68. Kb4 Kd2 69. Na1 Kxe3 $19 { [%cal Gf5f1] }) 66... Bd8 67. Nb4 Bb6 68. Nc2 Ba5 { Zugzwang again! } 69. Nb4 Ke1! $19 { 0-1 Black wins. } 70. Nc2+!? (70. Kxc3?! Ke2 $19) 70... Kd1 71. Na1 Kc1 72. Nc2 Kb2 $19 { [%cal Gb2c2,Gb2a3] } 0-1


