{ This game was played in Buenos Aires 1970, when Fischer had already become the strongest player in the world. He won this tournament with 15/17, 3.5 points ahead of the next contender. }
1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nf3 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 g6 6. e4 d6 7. Be2 Nxd4 8. Qxd4 Bg7 9. Be3 O-O 10. Qd2 Be6 11. f3 Rc8 12. Nd5 Nd7 13. O-O Nc5 14. Rac1 a5 15. b3 Bxd5 16. cxd5 Qb6 17. Rc4 Qa7 18. Rc2 Bh6! 19. f4 Rc7 20. g3 b6 21. Rfc1 Bg7 22. Bb5 Qa8 23. Qe2 e5!? 24. dxe6 fxe6 25. Rd1 Rd8 26. Bd4? { Weakens the dark squares. } 26... Bxd4+ 27. Rxd4 e5 28. fxe5 dxe5 29. Rxd8+ Qxd8 { A classic good knight vs bad bishop scenario. } 30. Bc4+ Kg7 31. Bd5 Nd7 32. Qf2 Rxc2 33. Qxc2 b5 34. Kg2 b4 35. Qc6 Nf6 36. Kf3 Qd7! 37. Qxd7+ { The endgame clearly favors black. } 37... Nxd7 38. Ke3 Kf6 39. Kd3 Nb6 40. Bc6 Ke7 41. h4 h6 42. Ke3 Nc8 43. Kd3 Nd6 44. Ke3 Kd8 45. Kd3 Kc7 46. Ba4 Kb6 47. Ke3 Kc5 48. Bd7 Kb6 49. Ba4 Kc7 50. Kd3 Kd8 51. Bc6 Ke7 52. Ke3 Ke6 53. Kf3 Kf6 54. g4?! { More pawns are fixed on light squares. } 54... g5! 55. h5 Ke7 56. Ke3 Kd8 57. Kd3 Kc7 58. Ba4 Kb6 59. Bd7 Kc5 60. Ba4 Nc8 61. Be8 Ne7 62. Ke3 Ng8 63. Bd7 Nf6 64. Bf5 { The starting position in Silman's book. Silman already believes that this is dead lost for white. The engine is not impressed. } 64... Kb5 65. Kd3 a4 66. bxa4+? { Fischer calculated the rest of the game out from this position. } (66. Ke3!? a3! { Fixing a further weakness on a2. } 67. Kd3 Kc5 68. Ke3 Ne8 69. Kd3?? (69. Bc8! Nd6 70. Ba6! { The engine's maneuver is necessary to prevent the knight jumping into c3 or c4. } 70... Kb6 71. Bf1 $10) 69... Nd6! 70. Bd7 { Preventing the knight from jumping to c3 via b5, right? } 70... Nc4!! 71. Be8!? (71. bxc4?! b3 $19) 71... Nb2+ 72. Ke3 (72. Kc2!? Kd4 $19) 72... Nd1+! 73. Kd3 Nc3 $19 { [%cal Gc3a2] }) 66... Kxa4 67. Kc4 Ka3 68. Kc5 Kxa2 69. Kxb4 Kb2 70. Kc5 Kc3 71. Kd6 Kd4 72. Ke6 Nxe4 73. Kf7 (73. Bxe4? Kxe4 74. Kf6 Kf4 75. Kg6 e4 76. Kxh6 e3 77. Kg6 e2 78. h6 e1=Q 79. h7 Qe5! $19 { [%cal Ge5h8] }) 73... Nf2! 74. Kg6 e4! 75. Kxh6!? (75. Bxe4?! Kxe4 76. Kxh6 Kf4 77. Kg7 Nxg4 78. Kg6 Nh6!! 79. Kxh6 g4 80. Kg7 g3 81. h6 g2 82. h7 g1=Q+ 83. Kf7 Qa7+ 84. Kg8!? (84. Kg6!? Qd4 85. Kf7 Qh8 $19) 84... Kg5! 85. h8=Q Kg6! $19) 75... e3 76. Kg7 e2 77. h6 e1=Q 78. h7 Qe7+ 79. Kg8 Ne4! $19 { 0-1 Black wins. } 80. h8=Q+!? (80. Bxe4!? Kxe4 81. h8=Q Qe8+ 82. Kg7 Qxh8+ 83. Kxh8 Kf4 $19) 80... Nf6+! $19 0-1


