1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e5 Nd5 4. c3 d6 5. d4 cxd4 6. cxd4 g6 7. Nc3 Nxc3 8. bxc3 Bg7 9. exd6 Qxd6 10. Qb3?! (10. Rb1 Nc6 11. Bd3 O-O 12. O-O e5 $10 { I didn't see how to make any progress here as white. }) 10... Nc6 11. Ba3 Qe6+ 12. Qxe6 (12. Be2) 12... Bxe6 13. Be2 Rc8 14. O-O O-O 15. Ng5 Bd5 16. Bf3 (16. c4?? Nxd4) 16... Bxf3 17. Nxf3 Rfe8 18. Rab1 Na5 19. Bb4 Nc4 20. Rfe1 e5 21. dxe5 Nxe5 22. Nxe5 Bxe5 23. Rbc1 (23. g3 b6) 23... b6 24. g3 a5 25. Ba3 b5 26. Kg2 f5 27. h4 Kf7 28. Rb1 Rxc3 29. Rxb5 Rxa3 30. Rexe5 Rxe5 31. Rxe5 Rxa2 32. Rb5 Ke6 33. Rb7 Rc2 (33... Rd2) 34. Rxh7 Kd5 35. Ra7 Rc5 36. Ra6 Kc4 37. Rxg6 Kb4 38. h5 a4 39. h6 a3?? (39... Rc7! 40. Rg7 Rc6!! { The best try for black. White would have to play extremely precisely to hold the draw. } 41. h7 Rh6 42. Ra7 Kb3 43. f3 a3 44. g4 fxg4 45. fxg4 a2 46. g5 Rxh7 47. Rxa2 Kxa2 48. Kg3 { And we enter a well-known drawn position. } (48. Kf3?? Rh4! 49. Kg3 Ra4 { And white can never push the pawn passed the 6th rank due to Ra8! })) 40. h7 a2 (40... Rc8 41. Rg8 a2 42. Rxc8 a1=Q 43. h8=Q) 41. h8=Q *


