1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Nf6 3. Nf3 Nxd5 4. h3?! { Obviously a slow move. I didn't want to commit to d4 because of Bg4 with hypermodern pressure on d4. } 4... Nc6 (4... c5! { The best way to punish white's slow play. Fight for immediate control of d4. }) 5. d4 g6 6. Be2 Bg7 7. O-O O-O 8. c4 Nb6 9. Be3 Bf5? (9... e5! { Attack the center now! } 10. d5 Ne7 11. Nc3 Nf5 $10) 10. Nc3 Na5!? { I admit I completely missed this during the game. It's a smart way to allow for c5. } 11. b3 Nc6 (11... c5 12. Rc1 (12. dxc5? Nbxc4!! 13. bxc4 Bxc3 $15) 12... cxd4 13. Nxd4 { The line I was expecting. Here at least black has taken a stab at white's center. }) 12. Rc1 a5 13. a3 e5 14. d5 e4 { The right idea, but it's just too late. } 15. dxc6 exf3 16. Bxf3 bxc6 17. Bxc6 Qxd1 18. Rfxd1 { White emerges from the trades with a clear pawn up and more active pieces. } 18... Rad8 19. Rxd8? (19. Bf4!? Rxd1+ 20. Nxd1 { White's pressure will probably net him one more pawn. } { [%csl Gb2][%cal Gf4c7] }) 19... Rxd8 20. Nd5 Nxd5 21. Bxd5 Bb2 22. Rd1! { A tactical save is required. } 22... Kg7 (22... Bxa3?? 23. Bxf7+ $18) 23. Bc1 Bc3 24. Bf3 Re8 25. Bd2?? { A clear mistake that allows black's rook too much activity. The queenside majority is not able to break through with such an active rook, and the game should be drawn. } (25. Be3 { I wanted to improve my bishop but was uncertain it would be enough. } 25... Bb2 26. b4 Bxa3 27. bxa5 { This position is actually completely winning because my rook gets behind the a pawn super quickly and my bishops control the squares in front of it. }) 25... Bxd2 26. Rxd2 Re1+ 27. Kh2 Rb1 (27... Ra1!? 28. a4 { Now the pawn majority becomes unhealthy and black should be able to hold here. }) 28. Bd1 a4!? (28... Kf6 29. g4 Be4 30. f3 Bc6 31. Kg3 { Probably also drawn. }) 29. b4 Ra1 30. Bxa4 Rxa3 31. Bc6 (31. Bd1!? { Stopping any Rb3 maneuvers. I missed this entirely. } 31... Rc3 32. c5) 31... Kf6 (31... Rc3 32. Bd5 Bd3) 32. b5 (32. Bd5?! Be6 33. Bxe6 Kxe6 34. Rd5 Rc3 35. Rc5 { I thought white was still pushing, but it looks doubtful because of how active black's king is. }) 32... Rc3 33. Bd5 Bd3! { Winning the pawn back by force! } 34. Bc6 Bxc4 35. Rd7 { The c7 pawn cannot be taken unless black's king steps on a light square. As long as he shuffles back and forth on dark squares, the game is drawn. } 35... Ke6? 36. Rxc7 Kd6 (36... Bxb5?? 37. Bd7+ Bxd7 38. Rxc3) 37. Rb7 Rb3 38. Be8! Bd5?? (38... f5 39. Rxh7 Bxb5 40. Bxg6 { Even though all the pawns are on the kingside, this is finally enough to win. }) 39. Rd7+ (39. Bxf7) 39... Ke6 40. Rxd5 { The king cannot take the rook because of Bxf7+ with the skewer. Black resigned. } *


