1. e4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. d3?! dxe4 4. dxe4 Qxd1+ 5. Kxd1 Bg4 { Black should be happy to enter this endgame. } 6. Nd2 Nd7 7. b3?! (7. h3! { If black wants to setup the correct pawn structure with a black pawn on e5, then he has to give up his good bishop. } 7... Bh5 8. g4 Bg6 9. Nh4) 7... e5 8. Bb2 f6 { Now black's pawn structure is perfectly intact. } 9. Be2 Bc5 { [%csl Gf2] } 10. Ke1 O-O-O 11. h3 Be6 12. a3 Ne7 13. b4 Bb6 14. Nc4 Bc7 15. a4 Ng6 16. Nfd2 h5 17. g3 h4 18. g4 Nf4 19. Bf1 Nb8 20. b5 Nd7 21. bxc6 bxc6 22. a5 Nc5 23. f3 (23. Ba3) 23... Rd7 24. Rh2 Rhd8 25. Ba3 Na4 (25... Bxc4!! 26. Nxc4 Nce6 { With the knight coming to d4, black has the much better pieces. } { [%cal Ge6d4] }) 26. Bb4 c5 27. Rxa4 cxb4 28. Rxb4 Rd4 29. a6 R8d7 30. c3 Rd3 31. Bxd3 Nxd3+ 32. Kd1?? (32. Ke2 { Necessary } 32... Nxb4 33. cxb4 { Black still has an advantage due to the bishop pair, but must prove it with precise play. }) 32... Nxb4 33. cxb4 Bxc4 34. Kc2 Bxa6 35. Nb3 Rd6 36. Kb2 Bb6 37. Rc2+ Kd8 *


