1. c4 Nf6 2. d4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Be2 e5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d5 Ne7 9. Re1 Ne8 (9... Nh5 10. Ng5 Nf4 11. Bf1 f5 12. g3 Nh5 13. exf5 Nxf5 { An interesting line that black can try. It's not at all a usual KID line, but it makes some sense. } 14. g4 Nd4 15. gxh5 h6 16. Ne6?? (16. Bg2 $10) 16... Bxe6 17. dxe6 Nf3+ 18. Kg2 Qh4 $19) 10. Bd3 h6 11. h3 f5 12. Nd2 f4 13. b4 g5 14. f3 { I began to feel very confident with my attacking chances. We're basically in a bayonet attack, but with black having a few tempi on the main lines. } 14... Ng6 15. c5 Rf7 16. Bb2 Bf8 17. Nc4 h5 18. Be2 Nf6 19. Kh2 Rh7 (19... g4! 20. hxg4 hxg4 21. fxg4 Nxg4+ 22. Bxg4 Qh4+ 23. Bh3 Bxh3 { Somehow I missed Qh4+ completely winning. In my mind, I misunderstood that white was about to defend with Rh1! }) 20. Rh1! Qe7? (20... g4! 21. hxg4 hxg4+ 22. Kg1 Rxh1+ 23. Kxh1 Nh5! { [%cal Gd8h4] } 24. fxg4 Ng3+ 25. Kg1 Qh4 { Black can continue an attack even without the rooks on the board. In my head, I was sure white was holding if the rooks were traded. }) 21. Kg1 Qg7 22. c6 b6 23. a4 a6 24. Qb3 Nh4 25. Kf2 Qh6 26. Rag1 Kf7 27. Nd2 Ke8 28. Ke1 Kd8 29. Kd1 Ke8 30. Kc2 Kd8 31. a5 b5 32. Kb1 $10 { The lichess engine evaluation is misled. Unless a sacrifice on b5 yields something, black is the only one who can make progress with g4. But g4 is no longer working, so it's a dead draw. } *


