4. c3?! { If white makes any other non-critical move, we have the same thematic reaction. } (4. a3?! { Another example of a dubious move for white. } 4... e5! 5. dxe5? Bc5! $17 { Again, with winning threats on g1 and f2. }) (4. Nc3! $10 { The best move. White must develop and threaten black's center to deal with black's "threat." }) (4. Bd3? Qxd4! { Yes this is a free pawn. } 5. exd5 Qxd5! $17 (5... cxd5?? 6. Bb5+! Nc6 7. Qxd4 $18 { Don't let this happen to you! })) (4. e5?! e6 $15 { With c5 next, black is in an improved French. } { [%cal Gc6c5] }) (4. Be3? Qxb2 $15 { Yes this is a free pawn. }) 4... e5! { Ripping open the a7-g1 diagonal makes sense, especially now that black has a lead in development. } 5. dxe5?! Bc5! $17 { Either Bxg1 or Bf2+ is unstoppable, displacing white's king. Black's lead in development is already noticeable. } *


