1. e4 c6 2. Bc4? { This sad move is common enough that we have to mention it. } 2... d5 { The normal Caro Kann strike in the center now comes with tempo. } 3. Bb3 { White is trying to sacrifice a pawn in order to gain some initiative. But our position is so solid that this doesn't work out for white at all. } (3. exd5?! cxd5 4. Bb5+ Nc6 $15 { A worse version of the exchange Caro Kann. White is wasting time moving the LSB. }) 3... dxe4 4. Qh5 g6 5. Qh4 Nf6 { Simple development is best. } 6. Nc3 Bg7 { Simple development is best. } 7. f3!? (7. Nxe4?! Nxe4 8. Qxe4 Bf5 $15 { Why has white moved their queen so many times in the opening just to help us gain time while developing? }) 7... e3! $15 { No nonsense. Now white will not get a lead in development, and all of black's pieces are coming out to normal squares next. } *


