{ Welcome to another instructive study by NoseKnowsAll. In this study, I will be going over the "how," "when," and "why" of exchange sacrifices. An exchange sacrifice is defined as willingly giving up a rook (5) for a knight (3) or bishop (3). In this study, we'll see how the point value of a piece does not always equate the true value of the piece. Soon, you'll have a solid grasp of when to sacrifice material for an advantage!

Please check out my other middlegame strategy studies as well:
* Knights | How to dominate your opponents! https://lichess.org/study/kI8ikTU4
* Bishops | Slice through the opposition! https://lichess.org/study/kNn68T8l
* Rooks | Infiltrate for activity! https://lichess.org/study/U7tTRtdj } { [%cal Ge3e6,Ge3b3] }
 *


