[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ Black has just played the mistake Na4. Can you punish their play? }
2. Nxa4! (2. Bd4? { After Bxd4+, Rxd4 Qb6!, Rad1 Nc5!! it is black who has the last laugh. } 2... Bxd4+ 3. Rxd4 Qb6 4. Rd1 Nc5!! $15) 2... Bxa1 3. e5! { Exactly! Black has won an exchange, but white is immediately breaking through in the center! } (3. c5?! { A reasonable idea, but black has the saving line: Be6! Qd1 d5!, and they can barely equalize. Don't allow your opponent to regain the initiative! } 3... Be6! 4. Qd1 d5 $10) (3. Bb6? { After Qf6, you have just improved black's queen. } 3... Qf6 $10) 3... Bf5 4. Rxd6 $18 { Yes, black is up the exchange, but it's unclear if the bishop on a1 will ever get out alive. Moreover, the central pawn mass gives white excellent winning chances even if we don't net the full bishop. } *


[Event "Always sacrifice the exchange!: Exercise 3"]
[Date "2020.11.29"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
