1. e4 { Notes by Dr. Tarrasch } 1... e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. O-O Nxe4 5. d4 Be7 { [%cal Gf8e7] } 6. Qe2 (6. dxe5 O-O 7. Qd5) 6... Nd6 7. Bxc6 bxc6 8. dxe5 Nb7 { [%cal Gb1c3] } 9. b3 O-O 10. Bb2 d5 11. exd6 { This gives away White's opening advantage by
consolidating the opponent's game. 11 Nbd2 was indicated. } (11. Nbd2) (11. c4 dxc4 12. Rd1 Qe8 13. Qxc4 { [%csl Gc6,Gc7] }) 11... cxd6 12. Nbd2 Re8 { ! The R here threatens the White Q, and it
is interesting to see how quickly that indirect menace gives
Black some decisive advantage. } { [%cal Ge8e2] } 13. Rfe1 Bd7 { [%csl Ge7,Ge8][%cal Gd2e4,Ge4d2] } 14. Ne4 { This turns
out to be ineffective. It would have been relatively best to
retreat the Q to f1, the only if modest place where she could
enjoy a little peace. } 14... d5 { [%cal Ge4g5,Ge4f6,Ge4d6,Ge4c5] } 15. Ned2 { The Kt mustn't go to g3,
since Bb4 would cost the exchange. } 15... Ba3 16. Be5 { [%cal Ga3b2] } 16... f6 17. Qa6 { White just manages to avoid the loss of a piece. } { [%cal Ga6a3,Ga6b7] } 17... fxe5 18. Qxa3 e4 { [%csl Ge4,Gd5,Gc6] } 19. Nd4 Qf6 { [%cal Gf6f2,Ge8f8,Gf8f7,Ga8f8] } 20. c3 Rf8 21. f3 Qg5 { One blow after
another Lasker plays with great strength. } 22. Qc1 Nc5 { [%cal Gc5d3] } 23. Nf1 { [%cal Gc1g5] } 23... Qg6 24. Re3 Nd3 { [%cal Ge3d3,Ge4d3,Gd7h3] } 25. Qd1 Nf4 { [%csl Gg2] } 26. Ng3 h5 { [%cal Gh5h4] } 27. Nde2 Nxg2 { ! Forcing
the issue with an elegant combination. } { [%cal Ge4f3,Ge3f3,Gh5h4] } 28. Kxg2 { [%cal Gh5h4,Ge4f3] } 28... Rxf3 (28... exf3+ 29. Rxf3 Rxf3 (29... Bh3+ 30. Kxh3 Qg4+ (30... Rxf3 { [%cal Gh5h4] } 31. Qd4 { [%csl Gd5,Gf3,Ga8][%cal Gd5g8,Gd5f3,Gd5a8] } 31... h4 (31... Rd3 32. Qh4 Rf8!) 32. Qxh4 Kf7 { [%cal Ga8h8] }) 31. Kg2 Qxf3+ 32. Kg1 h4 (32... Qf2+ 33. Kh1 Qf3+ 34. Kg1 h4) 33. Nh1 (33. Qd4 h3 { [%cal Gf3g2] } 34. Nf4 Rxf4 35. Qd2 Raf8 36. Nh5 Qh1+ 37. Kxh1 Rf1+ 38. Rxf1 Rxf1#) 33... Qe3+ { Resigns,
since Kg2 is punished by the pretty mate ...h3. } 34. Kg2 (34. Nf2 Qxf2+ 35. Kh1 Qf3+ 36. Kg1 h3) 34... h3#) 30. Kxf3 h4 { [%cal Gf3g2,Ga8f8] }) 29. Rxf3 exf3+ (29... Bh3+ 30. Kxh3 exf3 { [%cal Gg6g4] } 31. Qd4 Qe6+ 32. Kh4 { [%cal Gg8h7,Gh7h6,Gg7g5] } 32... g5+ (32... Kh7 33. Nxh5 g5+) 33. Kxh5) 30. Kxf3 0-1


