1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5 6. Ndb5 d6 7. Bg5 a6 8. Na3 b5 9. Nd5 Be7 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. c3 O-O 12. Nc2 Bg5 { [%csl Gc4][%cal Ga2a4,Gf1c4] } 13. Be2 { Probably not the best variation. The bishop belongs on c4 usually. } 13... Be6 14. O-O Ne7 { [%csl Gd5] } 15. a4 Bxd5 16. exd5 bxa4 17. Rxa4 a5 18. Qd3 $10 Qb6 19. Rb1 Qb7 20. Na3 { [%cal Ga3c4,Gc4d6,Gc4a5] } 20... Qxd5 21. Qxd5 Nxd5 22. Nc4 { [%cal Gc4d6,Gc4a5] } 22... Rab8 { [%cal Gd5c3] } 23. Raa1 (23. Rxa5? Nxc3 $17) (23. Nxa5?? Nxc3) 23... a4 { [%cal Ga1a4] } 24. Bf3 Nb6 { [%cal Gc4d6] } 25. Nxb6 (25. Nxd6?! Rfd8 26. Ne4 Be7 { [%cal Gf7f5] } 27. g4 g6 28. g5 { Gotta stop f5 from black or white is actually just worse. }) 25... Rxb6 26. Rxa4 { The passed b pawn is more important. Taking on d6 wouldn't have given us as much because that pawn is already blockaded anyway. } 26... Rc8 27. Bd5 { [%cal Gb2b4,Gb4b5] } 27... Bd2 28. c4 Rcb8 { [%cal Gb2b4] } 29. Ra7 { [%cal Gd5b7] } 29... g6 (29... Rf8? 30. h4 g6 31. g4 Kg7 { [%cal Gb1a1,Ga7d7,Ga1a7] } 32. Re7 h6 33. Ra1 Rxb2 34. Raa7 Kh8 35. Rxf7 Rxf7 36. Rxf7 Bb4 { Probably a draw in this variation as well. White is always pushing though. } { [%cal Gb4c5] }) 30. Rxf7 Kh8 31. h4 Rxb2 32. Rxb2 Rxb2 33. g4 Rb8 34. g5 Rd8 35. Kg2 { Black has to simply remain passive if he wants to avoid immediate death. } 35... h6?? 36. h5! Rg8 (36... gxh5 37. g6 { [%cal Gf7h7] }) (36... Bxg5 37. hxg6 { [%cal Gf7h7] }) (36... hxg5 37. hxg6 { [%cal Gf7h7] }) 37. Rd7 { [%cal Gg8g6] } 37... Rg7 38. Bf7 { 1-0 Black resigns. } { [%csl Gg5,Gg6,Gh6,Gh5] } 38... gxh5 (38... hxg5 39. hxg6 { [%cal Gd7d8] } (39. h6 Rh7 40. Rd8#)) (38... Bxg5 39. hxg6 { [%cal Gd7d8] }) 39. Rd8+ Kh7 40. g6+ Rxg6+ 41. Bxg6+ Kxg6 42. Rxd6+ { [%cal Gd6d2,Gd6g6] } 1-0


