1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 5. Nxf6+ gxf6 6. c3 Bf5 7. Nf3 e6 { This was the end of my theory. } 8. Be2 Rg8 9. Nh4 Bg6 10. O-O Bd6 11. Bf3 { The light-squared bishop may be outside of the pawn chain, but he's my captive as long as I can maintain my knight on h4. } 11... Nd7 (11... f5 12. g3!) 12. Re1 Qc7 13. h3 Bh2+ 14. Kh1 Bf4 15. Qb3 Bxc1 16. Raxc1 O-O-O { Seemed forced. I was ready to play Rxe6+ under other circumstances... } 17. a4 Kb8 18. Ra1 { Threatening a5-a6 to weaken the long diagonal. } 18... Bf5?? { He said how he needed to play something drastic in order to get chances to win this one. I was happy to give him the irish tripled pawns. } 19. Nxf5 exf5 20. a5 a6 21. Qxf7 Rdf8 22. Qb3 (22. Qxh7?! Rh8 23. Qxf5 { Why give him a ready-made attack when I can be happy with my pawn snack and better structure. }) 22... f4 23. Re7 Qd6 24. Rae1 (24. Re6!! { [%csl Gc7] } 24... Qc7 25. Rxc6! $18 { I completely missed this idea... } 25... Qd8 26. Rxa6 { [%cal Gb3b7] } 26... Qc7 27. Rc6 Qd8 { [%csl Gc6] }) 24... Rd8 { I knew I must be winning here, but I couldn't quite find the way forward... } { [%csl Gb7] } 25. d5!? (25. R1e6! Qc7 26. Rxc6 $18 { So simple and completely crushing. }) 25... Nc5 26. Qb4 cxd5 27. Qd4 (27. c4! { "I want my bishop's diagonal to open!" } 27... Ne4?? (27... Qc6 28. Bxd5 Qc8 $18) 28. Qxb7#) 27... Rd7 28. Rxd7 Nxd7 29. b4 Ne5 30. Qxd5 Qxd5 31. Bxd5 Rc8 32. Rc1 (32. Rxe5) 32... h5 { [%cal Gc3c4] } 33. c4 { Up a pawn and in a great endgame, I'm now dangerously low on time and I manage to mess it up immediately after missing Nd3 } 33... Nd3 { [%csl Gf2,Gb4][%cal Gb4b5] } 34. Rc2?? { [%csl Gf2] } (34. Rb1 Nxf2+ 35. Kg1 Nd3 36. b5 $16 { The queenside pawn chain is more important than the f2 pawn. }) 34... Nxb4 35. Rd2 Rc5 36. g4 hxg4 37. hxg4 Rxa5 38. f3 Nxd5 39. cxd5 Kc7 40. Kg2 (40. d6+ Kd7 41. Rd4 Rc5 $17) 40... Kd6 41. Kh3 Rxd5 42. Rxd5+ Kxd5 43. Kh4 a5 44. Kh5 a4 45. Kg6 Ke6 { 0-1 Black wins. } { Didn't even give me a chance to get the advanced pawn. } 0-1


