9... g6 { [%clk 0:00:22] } 20. Qf4 { [%clk 0:01:57] } 20... Rd7 { [%clk 0:00:20] } 21. h5 { [%clk 0:01:58] } 21... Kb8 { [%clk 0:00:18] } 22. g4 { [%clk 0:01:57] } 22... Rhd8?! { [%clk 0:00:17] } (22... Rc8 23. Qh6 c5 24. Qxh7 c4 25. Be2 { The rook belongs on the c file for the opening up of white's king. } { [%cal Gc4b3,Ga2b3,Ga5c7,Ge2d3] }) 23. Qh6 { [%clk 0:01:55] } 23... c5 { [%clk 0:00:16] } 24. Qxh7 { [%clk 0:01:48] } 24... c4 { [%clk 0:00:17] } 25. Be2 { [%clk 0:01:49] } 25... c3? { I needed to keep the c file open in order to infiltrate with my rooks. There's just not enough squares on the a file to penetrate with the light squared bishop covering a6. } { [%clk 0:00:15] } (25... Rc7 26. hxg6 fxg6 27. Qxg6 Rdc8 28. Qxe6 cxb3 29. cxb3 Rc2 { [%cal Gc2a2,Ga5a2] } 30. a4 Rxe2 $19) 26. Rd4 { [%clk 0:01:41] } 26... Rc7 { [%clk 0:00:12] } 27. hxg6 { [%clk 0:01:36] } 27... fxg6 { [%clk 0:00:12] } 28. Qxg6 { [%clk 0:01:38] } 28... Rc6 { [%clk 0:00:09] } 29. g5 { [%clk 0:01:17] } 29... Rdc8 { [%clk 0:00:10] } 30. f4 { [%clk 0:01:14] } 30... Rb6 { [%cal Ge2a6] [%clk 0:00:07] } 31. Rxb4 { [%clk 0:01:01] } 31... Qxb4 { [%clk 0:00:08] } 32. Bd3 { [%clk 0:01:02] } 32... a5 { [%clk 0:00:06] } 33. Qf7 { [%clk 0:00:49] } 33... a4 { [%clk 0:00:07] } 34. g6 { [%clk 0:00:51] } 34... axb3 { [%clk 0:00:08] } (34... Qd4!! 35. g7 axb3 36. axb3 Rxb3+ 37. cxb3 Qxd3+ 38. Ka1 Qc2 $19 { A sample variation of what happens if I had retained pressure on the bishop on d3. }) 35. axb3 { [%cal Gb4a4] [%clk 0:00:53] } 35... Rc5 { [%cal Gc5a5] [%clk 0:00:05] } (35... Ka7! 36. g7 Qa4 { [%cal Gb6b3,Ga4b3] } 37. g8=Q?? Rxb3+!! 38. cxb3 Qxb3+ 39. Ka1 Qa4+ 40. Kb1 c2+! { [%csl Ga4,Gc8,Gc2,Rd3,Rc1] } 41. Kb2 (41. Bxc2 Qxc2+ 42. Ka1 Qxc1+ 43. Ka2 Rc2+ 44. Kb3 Qb1+ 45. Ka3 Ra2# { An absolutely brilliant attack. These two lines are very similar to what I was attempting in the game, but show exactly how to execute properly. }) 41... Qb4+ 42. Ka2 Qb1+ 43. Ka3 Rc3+ 44. Ka4 Qb3+ 45. Ka5 Rc5+ 46. Bb5 Rxb5#) 36. Qf8+ { [%clk 0:00:44] } 36... Ka7 { [%clk 0:00:05] } 37. g7 { 1-0 White wins. } { I lost on time here because I couldn't see how the mate was coming. Indeed, it's too slow... the pieces are not able to get on the a file and finish the attack because of that hero light squared bishop. } { [%clk 0:00:45] } 37... Ra5?? { [%cal Gg7g8] } (37... Qa4?? 38. Qxc5) 38. Qxb4 1-0


