1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bc4 Be7 4. O-O Nf6 5. d4 exd4 6. c3 dxc3 7. Nxc3 O-O 8. Bf4 Nc6 { [%cal Gf1e1] } 9. h3 Na5 10. Bd3 Nd7 11. Qe2 Nc5 12. Bc2 Bf6 13. Rad1 (13. e5 { I thought about directly playing this move, but I figured the prep move Rad1 was stronger as I needed to involve all my pieces in any attack. } 13... dxe5 14. Rad1 Qe7 { [%cal Gc3d5] }) 13... b6 14. e5 Ba6 15. Qe1 Bb7?? (15... Bxf1 16. exf6 Qxf6 17. Bg5 Qe6 18. Qxf1 { I had visualized this line and thought the two pieces vs rook was a great exchange for me. } { [%cal Gb2b4] }) 16. exf6 Qxf6 17. Qd2 Nc4 18. Qc1 Rae8 19. Bg5 Qe6 20. Rfe1 Qd7 21. b3 Na5 22. Qf4 (22. b4 Bxf3 23. gxf3 Qxh3 24. bxc5 { I saw this line but I figured there was no need to complicate the game by going greedy when I was already up a piece. }) 22... Ne6 23. Qh4 f6?? { Never play f6. } 24. Qxh7+ Kf7 *


