1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. d4 O-O 5. e4 d6 6. Bg5 Nc6 7. Qd2 Bg4 8. Bh6? { Gives up the important d pawn after 2 captures. } 8... e5 9. d5 Bxf3 10. dxc6 Bxe4 11. cxb7 Bxb7 12. h4 Bxh6 13. Qxh6 Ng4 14. Qd2 h5 15. f3 Nf6 16. Bd3 Kg7 17. O-O-O e4 18. fxe4 Re8 19. Rde1 Re5 20. Bc2 Qd7 (20... Qe7 21. Nd5 Bxd5 22. exd5 Re8 23. Rxe5 Qxe5 { Surprisingly, fixing white's pawns is slightly better than the game because black controls the only meaningful file. }) 21. Nd5 Ng4 22. Bd1 Rae8 23. Bxg4 Qxg4 24. Nxc7 Rc8 25. Qxd6 Rxe4 26. Rxe4 Qxe4 27. Rf1 (27. b3 Qxg2 28. Rh2 Qe4 { With an even game still, although black is the one pushing due to the unsafe king. }) 27... Qxc4+ *


