1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Nf3 Bd6 5. Bd3 Ne7 { Knight belongs on e7 to support Bf5 and a trade of the black's bad bishop for white's good bishop. } 6. O-O O-O 7. Re1 Bf5 8. Nc3 c6 9. Ne2 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Na6 11. c3 f6 { Deciding the hole on e6 was worth less than the output on e5. } 12. Nf4 Nc7 13. Bd2 Qd7 14. Re2 a5 15. Rae1 Rfe8 16. Ne6 Nxe6 17. Rxe6 Ng6 18. Qe2 Rxe6 19. Qxe6+ Qxe6 20. Rxe6 Bc7 (20... Kf7! 21. Re2 { Up one tempo over the game. The bishop cannot be taken! } (21. Rxd6 Ke7)) 21. g3 Kf7 22. Re2 Re8 { Are there really any better winning chances for black by keeping the rooks on? By trading, white is left with two slightly worse minors and slightly less space. } 23. Rxe8 Kxe8 24. Kf1 Ne7 25. h3 Nc8 26. Ke2 Ke7 27. Nh4 g6 28. f4 Nd6 { Finally getting the knight to an active square. f4 stops the idea of Bf4 - trading dark squared bishops - a good move for white. } 29. Ng2 a4 30. b3 axb3 31. axb3 Ne4 32. g4 Ba5 33. b4 Bc7 34. Be1 Bd6 35. Kf3 { And draw was agreed by players. } 35... f5 36. Ne3 Ke6 37. Nd1 h6 38. Ne3 Be7 39. gxf5+ gxf5 40. Nd1 *


