1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Bd3 Bd6 5. Ne2 Nf6 6. Bf4 O-O 7. Bxd6?! { No need to help black's development. } 7... Qxd6 8. O-O Nc6 9. c3 Ne7 10. Nd2 (10. Qc2!? { A try to avoid the exchange of bishops. }) 10... Bf5 { The knight maneuver allows for black to offload his bad bishop as well. } 11. Bxf5 Nxf5 12. Qc2 Rfe8! { Activates the rook with tempo. } 13. Nf3?! { There's no need to give black the e4 square even for a move. } 13... Ne4 14. Rfe1 f6 { [%cal Gf6e5] } 15. Nd2 g6!? 16. f3 Ne3 17. Qc1 Ng5 { Objectively not best. But I wanted to keep as many pieces on as possible so as to avoid the draw. } (17... Nxd2 18. Qxd2 Nc4 19. Qc2 Re7 20. Ng3 Rae8 { The other line to consider. Black doesn't appear to have anything here though as all the rooks will come off and the c4 post is unstable. }) 18. Ng3 (18. f4) 18... f5! { Because the e4 square is out of bounds, I strive to create a new outpost for my pieces on e3! } (18... Qf4 19. Ndf1 { I thought this would lose a knight. But Nxg2 works here! } 19... Nxg2 20. Kxg2 Qxf3+ 21. Kg1 Nh3#) 19. Ngf1 Nxf1 (19... f4? { Too early here. The pawn will be lost. }) 20. Nxf1 f4! 21. Qc2 Nf7! { Heading directly for e3. } 22. Nd2 Nh6 23. a4 Nf5 24. a5 Qf6?! { Committing to an attack. I was hoping to avoid a fast Nf1 if I committed to the e3 outpost too quickly. } 25. Qb3 Ne3 26. Qxb7 (26. Nf1 { The move I was expecting. All dreams of a win end, and a draw is inevitable. }) 26... Qg5 (26... Reb8!? 27. Qxc7 Nc2 28. Qc5 Rd8 29. Rac1 Nxe1 30. Rxe1) 27. Rxe3?? { Like it or not, white had to try Re2 to offer any resistance. } (27. Re2 Nc2!? 28. Re5! Rxe5? 29. Qxa8+ Kg7 30. h4!! Qg3 (30... Qxh4 31. dxe5 Nxa1 32. Qxa7 Qe1+ 33. Nf1 Nb3 34. Qxc7+ Kh6 35. e6 Qxe6 36. Qxf4+ Kg7) 31. Nf1! Re1 32. Rxe1 Qxe1 { And after a sequence of only moves, white will be able to hold because of his hero defender Nf1 and the a pawn is soon to queen. }) 27... fxe3 28. Nf1? (28. Nb3 e2 29. Re1 Qe3+ 30. Kh1 Qf2 31. Qxd5+ Kh8 { The more obvious move also fails. }) 28... e2 29. Re1 exf1=Q+ 30. Rxf1 Qe3+ 31. Rf2 Rab8 32. Qxd5+ Kh8 33. Qa2 Qc1+ 34. Rf1 Re1 *


