1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Nc3 c6 5. Nf3 Bd6 6. Bd3 Ne7 7. Bg5 f6 8. Be3 O-O 9. Qe2?! { The queen appeared misplaced here, so I tried to take advantage of this with a quick attack down the e file. } 9... Nf5 10. O-O-O Re8 11. g4 Nxe3 12. fxe3 Na6 13. e4 Nb4 14. a3 Nxd3+ 15. Qxd3 Bxg4 16. Rhg1 Bxf3?! (16... Bf4+ 17. Kb1 dxe4 18. Nxe4 f5! 19. Nf2 Re3!! 20. Qc4+ Qd5 21. Qxd5+ cxd5 22. Nxg4 fxg4) 17. Qxf3 dxe4 18. Nxe4 Be7 19. Qb3+ Kh8? (19... Qd5!?) 20. Qf7? { Optically scary, but Bf8 defends all of the threats for now. } (20. Qxb7 { I figured this position would be fine for black because of the pressure down the b file, but it turns out there's nothing here, unlike in the game. }) 20... Bf8 21. Rg4 Qd5 22. Qxb7?? Rab8 23. Qxa7 Qa2!! { b2 is collapsing in every variation, and white's attack isn't fast enough to keep up. } 24. Rdg1 (24. b3 Bxa3+ 25. Kd2 Bb4+) (24. b4 Ra8) 24... Qxb2+ 25. Kd1 Rb7 { Misplacing the queen } 26. Qa4 f5! { And now there's no way out of this brutal fork. } 27. Nf6 fxg4 28. Nxe8 Qb1+ 29. Kd2 Qxg1 30. Qxc6 Qxd4+ 31. Ke2 Re7+ 32. Kf1 Qf4+ 33. Kg1 Re1+ 34. Kg2 Re2+ 35. Kg1 Qxh2+ 36. Kf1 Qf2# *


