1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 e6 { [%cal Ge7e6,Gd7d5] } 3. g3 d5 { He said he didn't like playing the french or open sicilian main lines. So we explored this one together. } 4. exd5 exd5 5. Bg2 { [%csl Gd5] } 5... Nf6 6. d3 h6 7. Bd2 Nc6 8. f4?! { Already I was happy as I'm thinking about potential light square weaknesses around his king. If I can trade off the super defenders (kingside bishop+knight)... } 8... Bg4 9. Nf3 Nd4 10. O-O Be7 11. Ne2 Nxf3+ 12. Bxf3 Bxf3 13. Rxf3 O-O 14. d4 c4 15. Nc3 Bb4 16. a3 { [%cal Gb4c3] } 16... Bxc3 17. Bxc3 Ne4 18. Bb4 { [%csl Gf8,Gd8,Ga8,Ga1,Gd1,Gf3] } 18... Re8 19. Qf1 { [%cal Ge4d2] } 19... a5 { [%cal Gb4c5,Gb7b6] } 20. Be1 b5 21. b3 Qf6 22. Rd1 Qd6 23. bxc4 bxc4 24. Qh3 Reb8 25. Qf5 Rb2 26. c3 Ra2 27. Bf2 { [%cal Ge4f2] } 27... Rxa3 28. Rb1 { [%csl Ge4] } 28... Rb3 { [%cal Gb1b3,Gc4b3,Gb3b1] } (28... Nd2 29. Rb7 Nxf3+ 30. Kg2 Qe6 { [%cal Gg2f3] } 31. Qxe6 fxe6 32. Kxf3 { Wins the exchange, but I figured my knight on e4 was stronger than the rook on f3. }) 29. Re1 Rxc3 30. Rxc3 Nxc3 { [%cal Ge1a1] } 31. Ra1 { [%cal Ga5a1] } 31... a4 32. Be1 Ne2+ 33. Kh1 Nxd4 34. Qh5 Nc2 35. Rd1 Nxe1 { [%cal Gd1e1] } 36. Rxd5 Qe6 37. Re5 Qc6+ { [%cal Gh5f3,Gc6f3,Gf3g2] } 38. Rd5 Rd8 { [%cal Ga4a1] } *


