1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. Bd3 Bxd3 5. Qxd3 e6 6. Nf3 c5 7. O-O? { Gives up the center. Can't be right. } 7... cxd4 8. Nxd4 Nc6 9. Be3 Qd7 (9... Nxe5 10. Qb5+ Nc6?? (10... Qd7! 11. Qxd7+ Kxd7 { The much stronger variation I missed. }) 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Qxc6+ { The line I saw. }) 10. f4 g6 11. Nc3 Nge7 12. Ncb5 Nf5 13. Nxf5 gxf5 14. Nd4 Rg8 15. c3 Be7 16. b3 a6 17. g3 h5 18. c4 dxc4? (18... Nb4 19. Qc3 dxc4 20. Qxc4 Rc8 21. Qe2 { A crushing variation that I underestimated in the game. Later, I wished I had this Nb4-d5 maneuver, but I underestimated the c-file pins. }) 19. Qxc4 Rc8 20. Rac1 h4 21. Kf2 Kf8?! { Trying to find safe-haven on g7, but the threats come way too quickly. } (21... hxg3+!? 22. hxg3 Ba3 23. Rc2 b5!? 24. Qc3 (24. Qxc6?? Rxc6 25. Rxc6) 24... Ne7 25. Qd2 Nd5) 22. Rfd1 hxg3+ (22... Qe8 23. Nxe6+ fxe6 24. Qxe6 Kg7!! 25. Qxf5 Rf8) 23. hxg3 Qe8 24. Nxe6+!? fxe6 25. Qxe6 Rd8 26. Qxf5+ Qf7 27. Rxd8+ (27. g4! { The only way to continue the attack. Push the pawns forward so that they're not blockaded on light square weaknesses. }) 27... Bxd8 28. Bc5+ Be7 29. Qc8+ Kg7 30. Qg4+ Kf8 (30... Qg6 31. Qxg6+ Kxg6 32. Bxe7 Nxe7 33. Rc7 { I couldn't allow this, so a draw was my best bet. }) 31. Bxe7+ Kxe7 32. Qh4+ Kd7! { Even though he walks onto the open file, the king will find safety near the pawn shield on the queenside. } 33. Rd1+ Kc7 34. Qh3 Nxe5 *


